My boyfriend rented a tuxedo from here for a black tie event. He was pressed for time and couldn't come in for a fitting before our event (I just picked up the tux on his behalf). He noticed as he was getting dressed for the event that the clasp on the pants was broken and as a result the pants were unwearable. He ended up not being able to wear the tuxedo at all because of this. What good is a tuxedo jacket if there are no pants to go with it? He instead wore a suit of his own, which was not ideal as it was not in line with the dress code for the event. We did call and let Top Hat Tuxedo know what had happened, and the man I spoke to told us he would run a full refund by his manager and make a note in the file about it. 

When I showed up to return the tux however, I was offered a $10 refund on a $90 rental (none of which he even wore). I was able to talk them into a $20 refund instead (anything more than $20 needs to be approved by a manager, meaning the man I talked to on the phone never followed through on his promise to do this). I was told that "most of these mistakes are usually caught during the fitting." The implication here was that it was somehow our fault that they did not catch the defect earlier in the process. I would think that all elements of the tuxedo rental would be inspected as the tuxedo was being assembled for rental. The fact that Top Hat Tuxedo apparently needed several opportunities to catch the defect is not my problem. In the end, the rental was a disappointment, but it was how bad and inconsistent the customer service was that ensured we won't be back.

I am going to dr. Amy Crump for nearly 10 years for dry eyes and various exams. Dr. Amy Crump is an amazing doctor that listens and spends time with you. Five stars completely for her alone. If I could give my doctor 10 Stars it would be her.

She is a doctor of Optometry and knows her stuff. She  spends as much time as possible and listens to every concern. I cannot leave there without just having the best feeling and always a smile.

I know this is a big firm. If Dr. Amy Crump went somewhere else I would follow her. She is that important to this practice and I hope the managers understand how wonderful she is.

The people cooking your food speak Vietnamese ~ that's a big hint that you'll be eating something pretty authentic! I've dined in twice, done takeout once and plan to bring my husband here soon.

The Spicy Beef Stew had good heat, broth was robust, hit the spot. But my delight came at the end of my meal: the waitress noticed I didn't finish the meat in my bowl (not because it wasn't tasty but due to my personal limits on meat consumption) and she said, "next time you don't like the food, let us know and we change it for you". Wow, that coming from an Asian restaurant tucked in a nondescript plaza - sure caught my attention!

The next thing that caught my eye was a picture of their Phnom Penh Dry Noodles on their takeout menu. Looked so much like my favourite Bak Chor Mee (minced pork noodles) from Singapore! So I went back the very next day to try it. Though it wasn't what I was hoping for, this would serve as my go-to dish next time I miss home. [By the way, if any of you find Bak Chor Mee in the greater Toronto area, please connect with me!]

The following week I decided to do takeout Chicken Pad Thai. Oh-my-goodness ~ it was Heavenly! The noodle stir-fry had dramatic flavours: generous lemongrass, sweet and mildly spicy. Balanced with just the right amount of crunchy veggies (raw bean sprouts + surprising dollop of pickled radish) and peanuts, I ate with relish. I think I would have punctuated my meal with "this is SO good" & several grunts of satisfaction, but I was out in public and yes, I'm shy.

The Spice Seeker that I am, I was THRILLED to see on the table 2 types of chillies you can add to your food: a chilli paste (milder) and pickled chilli slices (one thin sliver packs a huge punch!)

Amazing food, great service, free WiFi. No wonder this place is busy during lunchtime. Fun decor with a rustic Asian feel, the noise adds to the ambience. Cash & Debit only. Come early so you can get a parking spot in the plaza :)
Soo good. Breakfast burrito was fantastic, chicken salad so good. Great meat slices in all the foods . Great price and portion.

Stay away from Jan and Kerry Coffman!!!!   We rented from them and had a TERRIBLE experience.  If they are as bad of a realtor as they are as a landlord, watch your back.  Better yet, find another! On the final walk through, he said the house looked great.  He said we were great tenants and he was happy with the condition that we left the house. Then, when it came time to refund our deposit, he charged $114 to PRESSURE WASH the garage.  It had normal marks from parking a car in it.  Ridiculous!  He used flat paint in a rental, and then had the nerve to complain when there were scuff marks on the walls after 2 years of normal wear and tear.  No professional landlord who knows what they're doing would use flat paint in a rental, unless they're creating a reason to withhold your security deposit!  I own a rental home and I know better than to do that.  I never treat my tenants with such disrespect.  Disgraceful!  You can't keep flat paint clean and you can't wash it, believe me we tried.   He charged us $1100 to paint the house after normal wear and tear on flat paint, violating NV state law (NRS 118A.242 para. 4).   When we called to discuss this with him, he hung up on us...highly unprofessional! He highlights his veteran status, yet this is how he treats active duty military personnel.  Disrespectful!  Do yourself a favor and use someone else!  I'm TERRIBLY disappointed with them and would NEVER USE THEM AGAIN.

Marshalls is a place that I usually go for great deals on clothes specifically dress shirts but I don't really expect great customer service.  This one however in the dozen or so times that I have been in have had excellent people at the checkout counter.  This cannot be said for all Marshalls but because of it, I make my way here instead even though its further to drive.

A good solution to stay in Las Vegas and save some money thanks to the kitchen. But be careful, sometimes it's only a kitchenette with fridge and microwave. If you want more (ie hobs and oven), say it! We had a bad surprise when entering the room but the reception employee was very nice and changed immediately without any charge. Add $3 for cooking equipment (pans, etc.). Beside that, it was clean and good enough for our short stay. Walking distance to Strip.

-----

Une bonne solution pour rester à Las Vegas et économiser un peu d'argent grâce à la cuisine. Enfin, si vous en avez une, car c'est parfois seulement une kitchenette avec un réfrigérateur et un micro-ondes. Si vous voulez plus, comme des plaques et un four, il faut le signaler. Nous avons eu une mauvaise surprise en entrant dans le premier appartement mais l'employée de la réception a été très sympa et nous a immédiatement changé d'appartement, gratuitement. Ajoutez 3$ pour la vaisselle (casserole, poêle...). A part cela, c'était propre et bien pour notre court séjour. Strip accessible à pied.
Better than Pin Up Pizza, but nothing spectacular, just an average slice, especially when compared to New York pizza. The atmosphere is nice though with the music and the posters on the wall.

3.5* Decent ramen spot. Love the decor and the wait staff is attentive to your needs. 
About 30 seats + 6 bar spots. 
Great value when you're extra hungry. 
$13 will get you double meat (4 pieces) + 0.50 for an extra bowl of noodles.

Waitress suggested a warm peach tea (premium! $1.50) which was nice in this -18degrees weather. The peach fragrance was delightful. 

I asked for half lean pork and half chicken cha siu. Both were perfectly seasoned and not dry. They offer 4 types of soup base; I chose black but wasn't a fan of it. It was supposed to be garlicky, but not enough for me. it had more of a charcoal flavour than garlic. So I was a bit disappointed there. Can't beat Kinton's spicy garlic ramen...mmmm
Noodles were nice, though I would've preferred more al dente. 

Our kind waitress offered toragashi (sp?) pepper spice, which was not fragrant, and sriracha for my friend's chicken karaage. the karaage wasn't crispy enough... maybe the oil wasn't hot enough? Or their potato starch ain't cutting it. chicken itself was juicy and offered with mayo dipping sauce. 

Their flavours are decent, but the broth didn't satisfy my ramen cravings. I'd try it again, but it's not on my A-list.

When it comes to the Mt. Rushmore of fast food burger joints with a drive thru you will see the signs of In n Out, Whataburger, Culver's, Steak nShake and Wendy's. These joints serve fresh beef and that is criteria #1. Shake Shack, Habit, Smashburger and Five Guys don't have drive thru and have their own separate mountain. Culver's hasn't made it to my neck of the woods but if work drops me by a location I am always going to visit. The Butterburger is one of life's little treats.  Add a slice of cheddar and you are in business. A simple burger prepared exquisitely. Fresh beef nicely griddled and seasoned, a buttered and toasted bun, a touch of mayo, pickle and red onion. Symphony.  Watch out they are generous with the onion and that can overpower. The frozen custard puts just about every ice cream I have had to shame. My advice , if you see a Culver's, pull over immediately.

Me and my family ate here last night and I must say it was wonderful. It was my first time here so I wasn't sure exactly what to expect. Two of my cousins from Nebraska said their fish meals were some of the best they have ever had. I had a 7oz Sirloin and was cooked perfectly! As the rest of my family was ordering dessert, I chose a chocolate martini they had on special and it was pretty good. I thought the service was excellent, and it was a nice clean family restaurant. 
Overall, everybody was happy and we would go back.

Yesterday, I introduced my mom to Cafe Vito and she thoroughly enjoyed it too.

This time it was about savory we both shared a cold cut & cheese as well as a sausage pannini & each a latte.

Mom loves casual places and Vito's was no exception. 

It was novel for us to sit under the canape in the rain eating. We took 2 types of biscotti & the nutella cookie to go. Yum.

One star because I have to, otherwise this place would have negative stars! I have eaten at other Cracker Barrel locations an loved it, NOT here. After a very long wait and a really rude hostess we received awful food. My sausages were hockey pucks requiring a knife to cut them, my hash browns looked like I got the last bit out of the old pan, hard and overcooked (actually burnt across the top), and the biscuits were doughy and undercooked. Everyone raves that the portion sizes are huge, but it looked like they had used an oversize plate to serve me my two tablespoons of hash browns and my eggs. It took me another 15 minutes to get the rest of my breakfast! Service was lackluster and when we said something the server just put our check on the table and walked away. I will NEVER go back to this location, I'd rather drive an hour and get better food and service! Typical "Vegasizing" of an otherwise amazing establishment!
I wasn't feeling great when I went, but the service was good and the food was decent.  Will give it another chance when I'm feeling better:)

I find it hilarious that ABC is located smack dab the middle of the "newest, trendiest" part of town - and it does not give a shit. It's a dark dingy-dive that is slinging juicy burgs and that's all there is too it.  

We heard that this unassuming place had some of the best burgers in town - as far as classic burgers go - and it did not disappoint. I also loved that they had hand cut fries! 

Cheap. Delicious. Don't miss this spot for your late night burger craving.

I love Illy cafe, is the beast italian coffee in the world. Every time I'm at the Palazo Venetian hotel I stop at this place, and drink the beast cappuccino.
Make me fill in Italy.

I hate that I have to write this review because the food was excellent, my husband and I enjoyed everything we ate. And for a great price. However, the service we received was absolutely terrible. Our waitress came over two times in the entire hour and a half we were there, and the last half was spent waiting for our waitress to bring us our check. We finished our sushi, and wanted to order a fried ice cream for dessert, and a glass of white wine. As the time went by, we asked another waitress for another menu to order from. No one ever brought another menu over. Eventually, 30 minutes after finishing our food, we just asked another waitress to get our check for us, as our waitress was in the corner talking and laughing with her friends. We paid, and left without having received everything we wanted to get. I give four stars because the food was amazing, just don't expect good service.

Funky and chill, this place has a nice vibe when you walk in - you can tell that all of the folks there are working artists with distinct styles rather than generic tattoos of hearts with "Mom" written across the middle.  Went here with my sister while she got her tattoo done of a design that I drew - Misty was incredible and very chill.  When I gave her a couple of tweaks so that the design would match the picture (it's such a different medium from pen to tattoo needle that the lines come out differently), she made them perfectly and worked with me to get the design just right.  It was the perfect tattoo and it wouldn't have been so without her killer eye and great attitude.  Well worth a visit.

I don't even know what to say about this place. We had a party of 5, and were excited to try something new. When we sat down, our server asked us if we wanted still or sparking water to which we responded still. Fleur was billed as a French restaurant and we were quite excited. When we looked at the menu, we were quite surprised. It was a mishmash of all different cuisines and a couple of French dishes. Nobody in our party could find anything that looked good to them. We didn't want to be rude, so ordered the duck tourine and the carpaccio. Neither was great. Could only taste arugula with the carpaccio and we all laughed that the duck looked and tasted like canned cat food. The best part of the night was our bill. $100.  They charged us $30 for the "still" water which was just a bottle of Fiji water you could pick up at the grocery store for $2. Drinks were small and no refills and the food was not good. We laughed for an hour after we left about the water and took the bottle with us when we went somewhere else for dinner.

There are a thousand places to go to get good Mexican food in the valley. And esp late night places such as filibirtos or other birtos ... This place just has super nice and acomidsting workers so it puts it over the top for me .

I love Buckle but the staff at fashion show are SO pushy! The first time I thought they were just having a slow day or maybe training... But it's literally every time. We get it, you need commission. But asking me 4 time in 6 minutes if I need something is absurd. Yes, I know how soft your jeans are, you don't need to keep bringing me pairs to touch. I ended up leaving because I was being hounded and couldn't even look at something without being asked if I want to try it on. Give customers space to shop!

Stayed here a few times over the years, it's beautiful :) my only complaint is that next to the restaurant on the hill(I can't remember it's name) they blocked off the area just to the left of the parking lot that has an excellent view of the valley's downtown area :( it's a great spot for pictures. Other than that, it's even better than the Phoenician.

Holy crap! This is hands-down the best dive I've ever visited for Mexican food. You will not find a better place. When you pull up, you'll be skeptical...trust me. Try it. 

The restaurant is cash only and the dining area is outside, screened porch. Again, put that aside. You're not here because of any of that.

You are here because of the food. The food. The fresh made tortillas. The hand pulled chicken, the perfectly seasoned steak. The rice and beans that are lovingly made fresh daily. 

My son had the red chili burrito and has said on more than one occasion that it changed his life. He gets a far-away look on his face whenever he talks about it. 

The place is PACKED during the week with business people and on weekends--even more packed with locals. They know something you don't know yet...but you will...Norteno is the bomb. Go. Now. Seriously.

Always have the Ceviche it's delicious and the shining star of the meal. It's such a clean light dish. Absolutely adore the won ton chips that come with it. The neon multicoloured straws are a fun touch! The cesar salad it's also delicious! Good clean iced tea. Eventually I'm going have some of the super delicious looking cocktails!! Service is always very good and I like the open floor plan with the openness to outside.

Worst manager, bad service, bad attitude long,long,long wait then burnt pizza. When we asked for some discount or compensation nothing. He comes running out with a coupon lol REALLY? Like we would ever go back here again. Cory needs a crash course in customer service. Even if he offered a drink or 10% off for our trouble no a lousy coupon. lol

This restaurant is located inside Venetian hotel casino.

Having eaten in Hong Kong and Singapore at some of the best restaurants there, I would say that the chefs here are among the top chefs.

Try their beef noodle soup, this place makes the best beef noodle soup.  Sometimes it is a bit salty, just add a little red vinegar and it will taste better.

I would recommend you try the spicy wonton appetizer, Mongolian beef and scallion, wonton noodle soup (pay an extra $9-$10 to add the BBQ pork).  If you are vegetarian, try their stir fried string bean. 

It is pricey, but don't forget that you are in Vegas. 
$10 may not be enough for one hand of Black Jack, but it can buy you a good bowl of noodle.

My husband and I just moved nearby, and I don't think I am ever going to cook again.  I love this place!

The lunch specials are great--7$ for a soup, spring roll, and choice of entree.    The dinner prices are also totally reasonable. 

The food can be a bit on the spicy side--I usually like my food medium, but I always make sure to order it mild here.  My spice loving husband usually orders medium.  The spice is always nice a flavorful, not just a burn.  Yum!

The portions are large (we always come home with leftovers) and the service is great (my soda is always refilled before it's empty).  This is my new favourite place to take out of town visitors!

Finally made it to this wonderful eatery last evening. Service, excellent. Ambiance, Yardie was rocking LadySaw and some dancehall vibes. Food. I say again, THE FOOD!! Curry chicken was fabulous. Authentic. Tasty. The Jerk Chicken was deliciously spicy. Sides were perfectly prepared. The portions are huge. Hope they never change that!! Highly recommend. Be hungry!

I've searched high & low, there's nobody who does their lobster tail like this place. It's a big portion of fresh & tender filet of lobster without the shell, just the way I like it. And you gotta have it with house potatoe wrapped in wonton wrap. It's to die for!! I drive 4 hours to vegas just to eat my favorite lobster here, 'cus it's done right!!

Not bad! Baristas were a little unfriendly. I got an iced coffee that was strong but good. I also like that if you get a latte, there's no price difference between a single shot and a double shot of espresso. A girl's gotta have her caffeine!

I made my appointment online. I went in to be seen for a sore throat and possible sinus infection. I waited in the lobby for 10 mins and was seen by the medical assistant as soon as I was taken to the room. He was wonderful and very professional. Once he left the NP walked in no less than 2mins later. She was awesome! I am exclusively breastfeeding and everything she prescribed me she double checked to make sure it was safe for BF Moms. Overall I was taken care of and had a great experience !

If you're looking for cheap Asian eats, you've found your spot! However, beware that any restaurant serving Thai Chinese & Japanese (three very different cuisines) isn't really going to be the best/most authentic at any of them! I went here for lunch and got a Thai green curry. Definitely not the best Thai food I've tasted, but it's cheap enough that I'd consider coming back if I'm in the area and starving. My friends said the same about the Chinese dishes they ordered. In a city boasting a variety of authentic Asian restaurants, not sure why anyone would pick this place except cost.

Excellent food but horrible service. The first dishes were brought out after about 15 minutes of ordering, but the second round of dishes were brought out one hour after that. We were still hungry but did not order more as we did not want to wait for another hour. No apologies or explanation was provided for the delay. 

The wait staff did not seem trained as they removed the plates before we were done without asking us if we were done. 

Would not come back and would not recommend, even though the food was good.
The staff couldn't be sweeter and in a better mood. From the busser/food runner to the register people they're all good at what they do. The outside seating is always nice too. Great place!

Came here again and was surprised to see the newly renovated restaurant. I was told by the waiter that the owners have changed but the chefs are the same. The Wan Tan Hor Fun is delicious as before. I like that the restaurant is much brighter and more spacious now. Thumbs up!

Friendly service combined with the most affordable daily car rental prices I found in Brampton.

Booking was very easy online via their website. Although distance is limited to 300km per day, it's a great option if you only plan on traveling within the GTA.

I paid $45 to rent an intermediate size (mid-range) car for one day (Chevy Cobalt). Other agencies were charging about $65-85 for a comparable model. LDW was covered by my Amex, so saved about $20 there.

Best part is they provide a pick up and drop off service anywhere in Brampton.

Best pupusas I've ever had. Be prepared to wait 15 or 20 minutes for your order as they are made fresh. I usually call ahead or leave and grab a few things in the market and come back cuz the seating is often scarce and cramped.  Tried their tacos and they were average so my advice is to stick to the papusas and leave the tacos to Seven Lives.
For downtown this was a great experience.  Free parking, nice friendly staff were everywhere for whatever question you had.   NIce pool and water slide too.

Deal of the century! OK well maybe not the century, but most things are at 50% off between 9 to 10 PM. They obviously want to start fresh the next day so it's a great way of them getting rid of their food and us getting a crazy good deal. The food is also pretty damn tasty! Good thing my first two yelp dining choices closed earlier. Had I known I would've been here in a heartbeat.

Like a lot of first timers, I was a bit hesitant about being naked around women I didn't even know.  My sister felt a bit uneasy with it at first, but she agreed to get a massage while I did the go at your own pace stuff.

There is a separate entrance for men and women.  They give you two towels and a "gym outfit" which is basically the most unflattering thing ever.  It's a hospital scrub-like top and then these stretchy linen shorts.  Then you also get a key to a locker. 

The locker room/lounge was very nice.  They had comfy chairs and several women were there napping or just watching tv.  They had a lot of amenities, including disposable razors, individually wrapped toothbrushes, hair products, etc.  It felt like they had put a lot of thought into what to make available.  Right off the lounge is the entrance for the upstairs area for both men and women, which I will get to.  There was also a dry salt sauna.  When you enter the glass door there, you enter the main spa area.  Immediately upon entering, there is a dry suana ahead and showers to your right (you have to shower before going in anywhere and anytime after you get out of a sauna).  To the left there is a warm tub with jets, a hot tub, a cold water tub, a salt steam sauna and a eucalyptus sauna.  Pro tip: if you are new to one of the "wet" saunas, sit on the bottom step.  It will not be as hot since the steam rises.  Also, breathe through your mouth and not your nose and just stay in for a couple minutes.  There was also a section of little showers where you could sit on a stool close to the ground.

The upstairs area was nice, but I hated having to wear my gym outfit.  The rooms were hot and I didn't feel like adding polyester blend to the mix was relaxing.  Also, they have signs posted, but let me just tell you: BE CAREFUL WHEN YOU STEP INTO THE CLAY BALL SECTION.  I don't know why, but I thought the signs meant "be careful when you step in the room" as opposed to "be careful when you step on the heaping pile of clay balls."  Yeah, I'm an idiot.  Anyway, I fell and woke up a very nice Asian man who asked me if I was ok.  I was, but I decided to beeline out of there and decided that the ice room would be the best option.  It's basically like a walk in freezer that you sit in, though it wasn't quite as cold as a freezer.  I got to talking with someone in the ice room and completely forgot that I had left my sister and her massage had ended 45 minutes earlier.  I was so worried that she would be mad at me, but when I looked for her, I found her completely naked, in the cold tub, talking gingerly with another woman.  I honestly don't know what it is about this place, but it was very freeing to be able to walk around with no clothes on and my sister ended up loving it, even though she was initially scared to be naked.  She said her massage was incredible, as well.

Honestly, this was the highlight of my trip to Vegas.  If you are thinking of coming here, please do.  It can be intimidating at first, but it was so, so nice and relaxing and freeing.  I've added this to my must do list when I come back in town.

I went into T Bird to look at some watches this afternoon. I spoke with Alexia in regards to a few different Rolex models that they had in stock. She was very knowledgeable with the brand and answered all my questions. I also spoke with Darryl the owner of Tbird about watches and had a great time. I highly recommend this store for any jewelry needs. I will be back in the future for more purchases!
Guy was on time, called 40 mins before arriving. He spent 3 hours debugging and fixing.  He cleared the tree roots out of the pipes. Good work.  A bit pricey, but you get what you pay for.

A lot of times when I'm in Vegas I'll gamble for long stretches without eating, so by the time I am ready to eat I'm usually;

A) famished

and 

B) broke

When that happens, nothing fits the bill better than Tacos Mexico.  The tacos are great and not only that, but they're dirt cheap, typically ~$1.00-1.25 apiece, depending on what kind you get.  I'll stop there for breakfast (yes, breakfast - they're open 24/7) and have 6 or 8 tacos.   For about $10 I'm stuffed.

One of the best things about Tacos Mexico is that you can get tacos made with a lot of exotic meats that you don't find at many places.  Instead of just the usual beef/chicken/fish tacos you can also get tripe, cabeza, intestine, tounge meat, etc.   They also make an awesome bowl of menudo (tripe soup) for ~$6.

As many have noted, this place is kind of dumpy but who cares?  If I want to take my wife for a fancy meal then I'll go to a nice steakhouse or one of the fancy buffets, but when I'm by myself and just looking for some quick, cheap, tasty food, Tacos Mexico is my first choice in Vegas.

Efficient and delicious with a great menu. We tried their pastrami Rueben, turkey sandwich and vegetarian delight. All were good. Size OD sandwiches: not too big, not too small, just right. Reasonable prices, great service. And again, very efficient - I didn't have to wait long at all.
Jaycob is awesome! Very helpful! This place rocks!! I recommend this place for everyone. Tons of Fun for Kids.

I'm not sure what was the issue with our order but we did not like our food. It was so disappointing. My husband and I ordered chicken sandwich and the reuben sandwich. We also got a rotisserie chicken that was very good but pretty small for the price. The sandwiches were just not tasty. We both could not finish it. The reuben had too much of a vinegar flavor and the chicken had some strange stuff in it that made it hard to eat. The ingrained side by side would have been better than all together into a sandwich. I can only explain by saying the ingredients didn't mix well. The banana pudding was small, expensive and ordinary. Nothing really special about anything. We spent about $43 on dinner and couldn't even enjoy it. :(

Two+ stars for the rotisserie chicken. The rotisserie chicken saved for us or we would have been very hungry after our 35 minutes drive each way here.
Ali was fabulous with neck massage too. A special hour, made me feel like a new woman.

Ganadara is the best place for Korean food in Montreal. While there is always a line-up, it is definitely worth it. If you come alone or as a couple, the wait shouldn't be too bad, but groups of 3 or more need to be patient. However, once seated, you get your food very quickly and service is overall great. Prices are super reasonable and they have an alcohol licence. I recommend taking about 3 plates for 2 people. Only downside is the place could be bigger! 

My personal favourites are the tteokbokki (they have a crazy cheese version) and the bulgogi kimbap!

Always a good place for breakfast. Now dont get me wrong its the same thing over and over again but if you want the traditional eggs and some form of swine. This is a decent place for breakfast. Lunch and dinner have been ok as well. You can't beat $7.99 for breakfast. We joked around saying for that price you'd be lucky to get a decent meal at McDonalds. Oh and servers here have always been super nice and has helpful as possible for the amount of people they handle. A good fall back place for the days you can't decide what you want.
Absolutely outstanding, 10/10 authentic food. The ambiance really gives it a big boost.
The barista, Bobby, absolutely made my morning. The crew here in the mornings are very fast and are on point with everything I order. Definitely my regular Starbucks now!!!!!

Called in a large Lucky's Meat Lover's Pizza and 25 medium wings for pick-up on a Friday night at 6:30pm.  Was ready in 20 minutes, hot and fresh.   Generous amounts of toppings on the pizza as described on the menu and the wings were served with a twangy buffalo sauce and tasty ranch dressing.   Everything was delicious at a very reasonable price.   Lucky's is our new to-go pizza place from now on!

As a surprise, my husband took me to the Surprise Fine Arts and Wine Festival last weekend.
It is an annual event; next year it will be their third and we would both highly recommend attending it.

Having never been to Surprise, AZ before, we had no idea where to dine, so I checked-in with Yelp. 

We realized we were close to Babbo and decided to give it a try.
Yummy! 
Great crusty bread, helpful waiter, good service and reasonable prices. As I was leaving, I grabbed one of the take-with menus and realized that they have six locations in the Valley.

We'll definitely be looking for them.

What can I say, This place has great service not to mention awesome food. Things to mention here are the chicken katsu with curry. This is the best japanese curry that I have found to date! The shoyu ramen is awesome as well. If you want to try an app try they pork gyoza.... enjoy

I had a really fun time getting my hair colored for the first time at Philip Pelusi! I decided to go very light blonde and treat myself to a deep conditioning and protein treatment, which I highly recommend! Overall, I love the color, it is bright and the cool tones that I have been dreaming of. I loved working with Lacey, she did a great job, was super kind and gave great advice! Thank you for making my week special! :)

This is the best Mexican food I've ever had in Arizona. The portions are reasonable and so are the prices. The food is fresh and they don't overdo it on sauce and cheese. My kids loved it. Looks sketchy from the street and the decor is outdated but I would definitely come here again.

Turns out I was not the only person who got a Groupon to join the class today.
I was worried I couldn't find the place, but it was right on the first floor with a huge sign that was widely visible from the outside. 

The entrance has a tiny cubby where you can put your shoes. You hang your coat right on top it and then you're greeted by an overly eager and enthusiastic receptionist. They have a tiny selection of yoga matts, clothes and accessories for purchase and there's hot flavoured decaf tea you can drink after the session. I tried the lemon and it was delicious! There's incense burning and you get a general good feeling about the ambience. 

Who said the room is not hot? The guy next to me was dripping sweat by bucket. *metaphor intended* But seriously, that room is like a freaking sauna for those who haven't been to hot yoga before! There were about 30 people in the room and there was almost enough space between the mats. I could not believe how challenging hot yoga could be and that power flow class definitely made me breathe heavily and even stop at some poses so I don't faint.

The instructor was a young girl and she was very precise and helpful in adjusting the beginners. 
The bad part of the experience was the tiny change room and I believe there were only two showers for over 20 women who had just stepped out of the class. They didn't have paper towels, just two regular brown towels. 

Overall, I think this was a good experience considering I had never done hot yoga before. They say Moksha classes are less difficult, so I'll just stick to those for now.

Look. It is hard for me to comprehend a bad review of this place. From the seating to the chips and salsa to the margaritas to the main course through to the flan. Positively brilliant. Could not have been better. Bitching about coupons and oooo I used to live in LA...give me a break...this is the real deal done correct-a-mundo!

Saturday, February 1st - Calvin Harris. 

Our Hakkasan experience was AWESOME because we really got hooked up. Comp upper-level table and drinks for half the night with superb waitress service, then table right by the dance floor with Dom Pérignon champagne and fresh fruit, plus Grey Goose vodka shots galore. Couldn't have asked for a better night. 

Music was BLARING though, but I was entirely sober. Hakka gets incredibly (I'm talking sardines) crowded, but all in good fun. Might rub elbows with some celebs, whether Chris Brown or Singaporean pop stars. Say what?

I got a little lost when I arrived but the entrance is in the back along with the parking lot. Attended for a friends birthday. They have some appeasing appetizers and entrees but this place is definitely known for their craft and drinks. Service was great and they accommodate group reservations. Check out their option to take a bottle of brew home!
Sushi was fresh an tasty. One of the restaurants you can use your $20 food credit  you receive at check-in. Nice atmosphere and staff.

Fun fact: hachi means "8" in Japanese and is considered a lucky number.

Would this be my lucky day for ramen?  I was excited to try out this place since I saw the signs go up in this shopping center. We got here on a Friday night and were quoted a 30 minute wait but actually got seated in maybe 10-15 minutes. Seating is a bit limited as the shop itself is small. 

The namesake "hachi" or 8 refers to the number of ingredients in a bowl of their ramen. There are currently 4 different types to choose from: Shoyu, tonkatsu, miso, and the hachi special which comes with more chashu pork and egg. Note that getting the miso ramen or combination is an extra dollar versus getting the shoyu or tonkatsu. After browsing through their menu I decided on the miso ramen karaage combination and tried some of the tonkatsu ramen. The combination includes a side of karaage chicken, rice bowl, and a small bowl of bean sprouts in addition to the ramen of your choice. 

When I got my ramen I was disappointed that there weren't any slices of pork in it, despite paying an extra dollar. On the menu too it states that the ramen bowls come with your basic toppings: 1 piece chashu, 1/2 flavored egg, black mushroom (Or corn, bean sprouts), 1 piece dry seaweed, and green onion so I was expecting some kind of meat at least in the bowl. I thought at first a brown clump spotted on my ramen was maybe ground meat but it turned out to be miso paste. The flavor of the broth itself was very light, and the bowl had the thicker, yellow crinkled kind of noodles. Quite honestly I didn't really enjoy the flavor that much and the only thing I liked about the bowl was the lovely 1/2 egg which was marinated in soy sauce with a deep gold colored soft yolk. The tonkatsu ramen I tried did have the piece of chashu pork in it which was flavorful and tender, and it came with the thinner, straight, more pale noodles that look similar to what they serve at Tampopo Ramen. 

The karaage chicken was lightly battered, very juicy and tender. 

If I came here again I wouldn't get the miso ramen again due to the higher cost for value but maybe another variety of ramen from here will be better!

I have been going to the same Thai restaurants in Toronto (eg Pai, Sabai Sabai, Thai Basil) and decided to try something new.. and boy was I pleasantly surprised! 

I ordered the Panang chicken and my friend ordered the beef Khao Soi. The flavours of both dishes were phenomenal. The menu says the Panang curry is spicy but I felt it was pretty mild (considering that I do not take heat well). We ordered the ice cream dessert dish that they had and we did not feel that it was worth the price. We also tried the dark roast Thai ice tea which tasted like grass jelly... if you're looking for the flavours of a traditional Thai ice tea I would not suggest it. 

Only half their tables were filled on a Wednesday night --I prefer this because it allowed for conversation to take place at a comfortable noise level. Overall the waiter was attentive and the food was really good! I will not think twice about coming back!

WOW! I got into an accident 4 weeks ago. Luckily only the back quarter panel was damaged. My car has now been returned to me and I am beyond impressed and happy with the work Larry Miller provided. The attention to detail is outstanding! Larry Miller is all about making the customer happy, placing themselves in the customer's shoes and ensuring the vehicle passes all inspections. The highest priority to Larry Miller Collision is the safety of the car which I greatly appreciate. I am going to give huge kudos to Jennifer who assisted me the entire way with consistent phone calls keeping me up to date. Jennifer is a wonderful asset to the Larry Miller organization--she is such an awesome professional! Regarding Larry Miller Collision--TOP NOTCH AND HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!!
Good place to try Syrian style food. Just not my favorite. Average price 20-25 per person

This hotel should really be 2.5 stars, maybe 3 stars at best. It looks like it's stuck in the 90s and had the amenities and decor to show for it. The place smells and is dirty. The doors hadn't been cleaned in a while, and the rooms are outdated. There are pictures of jazz musicians/scenes throughout the hotel and rooms, but the decorations are supposed to be tropical. It doesn't make a lot of sense. The bathroom was not clean and the towels had dirt spots on them. This was my first time in Vegas and this hotel left a very poor impression.

We took our daughter out for dinner for her birthday. The food is always amazing!!! We can never go wrong! However our server Angel forgot about us...the girl that brought our soup and salad's asked us if we needed anything. We told her we needed bread and suddenly Angel appeared. He told her "I got it I will get their bread" and we also needed refills on drinks. After a while after that Angel was nowhere to be found so we proceeded to walk to the bar to get refills and then waited a while before he suddenly appeared asking if we needed anything else.....yes bread which we already requested and would've already had it if he would've just let the girl that served us our soup and salad bring it to us.
Food was amazing! Service was poor!!!

Montreal smoked meat!!!  Omg so good!  Who would have thought to find decent smoked meat in a chinese plaza in Markham.  Dudes are really nice.  Soccer was playing on the television when we were there.  It's not as good as my favorite in Montreal, but I'm happy to save a ton of time and gas to go to Markham for a similar product.  Must try the smoked meat poutine.  Also, I wish they would change up their rye bread provider, as I found it a bit hard and dry.

Note: Even my picky toddler wanted "more please", and they were so nice to her.
APDO is the best! They make my son comfortable with the process and make sure it's a fun experience for him.  Everyone in the office goes the extra step to make the visit go smoothly.

I'm not a huge fan of buffets so maybe I'm not the review to trust. But overall this is a typical American buffet, too salty, too sugary, no special flavours to speak of, and you leave with nothing but regret and a lighter wallet. They had some decent chicken potstickers and chow mein noodles, but that was about it.

From the outside, it looks like a deli/corner store. On the inside, it has a shipwreck vibe if that makes any sense. Low ceilings, dimly lit, kind of dingy but in a pleasant way. Cheap drinks and very cheap food that is tasty and has just the right amount of spice.

The vegetarian platter will feed 10 people! Ok maybe not 10 but easily more than 2...and it is $10. No tax??? Ok. The veggie platter is also good for take-out. It will feed you for days.

The owner of this restaurant is the sweetest person you'll ever meet! I had a large number of dumplings and potstickers catered from Little Szechuan and the owner gave me her recommendations as to what she thought people would like. They were made on time, fresh, and tasted amazing!! She also includes a sauce that's to die for it's the best sauce I've ever had with dumplings and potstickers and I have dumpling making parties at home with my friends and family. If you're in the area, dumplings are the best thing to get here! The other dishes are Szechuan style and delicious as well! I will definitely be coming back wanting to try more.

Boyfriend and I met his parents here on a beautiful Saturday morning. The place was packed, but since it's an order at the counter, take your number to the table place, there was no problem finding a spot on their sunny-yet-shaded patio.

I appreciate that it's semi-self serve, because that means I can refill my coffee as much as I want and grab any condiments I want (Cholula! Varieties of Tabasco! Ketchup!), but I think the price-point is a little steep for this type of service. Almost $50 for 4 at breakfast? I dunno. Seemed a little ridiculous.

{Side note: What irked the HELL out of me was watching people bark at the food runners to go back in multiple times for silverware, napkins, etc. GET IT YOURSELF. IT'S RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOUR FACE WHILE YOU FILL YOUR SODA. THESE PEOPLE ARE CLEARLY BUSY. YOU ARE LAZY.}

My omelet had a really tasty combo of roasted veggies, and I loved the way the zingy sun dried tomatoes played off the fresh mozzarella. The roasted rosemary potatoes were tasty enough, although Wildflower's are better in my opinion. Toast was toast. Get your choice of jellies when you go pick up your own silverware and napkins, because you are not a dick and can do it yourself.

The place was slammed by the time we left, but all the staff was still as smiley as can be. I just can't get past that price point though. If we were back in the area and hungry, I'd certainly try it again...just with someone else footing the bill.
Decided to try something new and could not have been more pleasantly surprised. Delicious drinks and food and amazing, friendly service.

My fiancé and his brother got a place through an agent named Landon Harris. He (Mr. Harris) was friendly and professional from the start. He was very prompt in responding to Joe's texts about any issues he and his brother were having. During their stay, Mr. Harris was on top of every issue that needed to be dealt with. When my fiancé and his brother moved out, Mr. Harris went beyond his duties to make the move out transition as easy as possible. They even got most of their deposit back. We definitely recommend Landon Harris for any housing needs.

I was having a party and decided on serving Polish food.  I had lunch here the previous week and the food was just as good or better than I could make.  So I decided to order  stuffed cabbage rolls, pierogis and fresh sausage.  Natasha was wonderful; she prepared my order when I arrived and also gave me directions on how to prepare and reheat the food.  I was having a total of 17 people for dinner and they all raved about how wonderful the food was!  I would highly recommend!,  they do have a small dining area with only four tables , so if they are busy you may need to wait for a table, but it is well worth it.  I live in the northeast valley and I will gladly travel to Mesa to enjoy their wonderful food.  Thanks Natasha my party was a success because of your food!
First time trying North End and I have to say it is now my favorite pizza place in town. We had the white pizza and Margherita - both were amazing!!! We will definitely be ordering again soon!!!!

We got a newly renovated room with hard beds and the drains are clogged, and  the large cover for the air conditioner kept falling of and hitting the floor all night. . I had to go buy a candle due to the smell... then  coming back up i got stuck in the elevator. We could have stayed somewhere much nicer for less money, and we are stuck here for another night. very disappointed especially since we are here for our aniversary. The second room we were moved to was even worse. it smelled and the shower was clogged so bad it had a foot of water in it. The manager Shelley offered us late check out as an answer to the problem.... Why would I stay here any longer than I had to. I regret staying here and they obviously don't care about their guests...

Hands down the worst experience I've had with an apartment complex.  Management turns over every year, maintenance is nowhere to be found, and they will nickel and dime you the entire time you're there (especially when you move out) citing a contract that they consistently break but expect you to follow. They even charged us for their rat problem/clean up and new appliances that they wanted to install after we moved out. Unreal. Would not recommend this place to my worst enemy.

I would not recommend anyone going to Anthem pet medical center, and I myself will never go there again.

The first time I went there, was just for a check up on my new puppy and to get her up to date on all her shots.  I saw Dr. Sabo, she was fine.  At the end of my visit when I went to pay my bill, there were two ladies sitting at the front desk, one who was just with me in the other room, and another lady.  They both ignored me.  I waited for 5 minutes, till I finally said I needed to pay my bill and then they both blamed the other person.  So I went back three weeks later for the one last booster my puppy needed.  First of all, the assistant was very rough with my puppy and made her cry just over getting her temp.  Next I saw Dr. Cohen who tested my puppy for blindness, then spent the next five minutes discrediting spay/neuter clinics and trying to get me to have my puppy spayed with them.  All I wanted was the booster, went to the front desk to pay my bill and they charged me $24 for the exam with the Dr. which I didn't even ask for, could have told them my puppy wasn't blind and didn't need to pay them for advertising to me that they were better than a spay/neuter clinic!  I told the lady all I scheduled was a booster, not an exam.  She responded we are not allowed to give puppies boosters with out an exam by the doctor.  I told her when I scheduled my appointment the lady should have informed my there was going to be an exam.  Then her answer was well you can sign a waiver not to have an exam.  So I said didn't you just say it was mandatory?  So now she tells me she needs to call the Dr.  When she gets off the phone, her answer was no we cannot take off the exam it is mandatory.  They lost my business right there!  And on top of that they had the nerve to give me an estimate of a spay for my puppy with all these random charges, including a micro chip implant which my dog already has and they know that!

So I will never go to them again, and would not recommend them.  I felt ripped off, disrespected by their rude staff and customer service is not one of their priorities.

one word: Excellent. 
The atmosphere, service, meal and drinks were all excellent. A must try. Great for a date.  I recommend the chicken adona with yogurt sauce. Love it.

Awful service and they never get your order right.  When I contacted the restaurant about how I was missing items from my order, they offered a coupon for 2 free meals (not that I would ever go back!) 
Their Farmer burger was underwhelming, unseasoned, and COLD. 
This establishment has some major issues; until they are resolved, I am never coming back.
Drunken noodles and Thai ice tea are phenomenal!  Everything else is delicious also.  I highly recommend this place!

This place was recently voted the 3rd  Best Restaurant for Comfort Food in Charlotte. We've been going there for years now, at least once a week and every Saturday for breakfast. This is one of the few places you can get authentic "home-cooked" meals that are excellent!!! Great Greek family --friendly and make you feel at home.  Prices are incredible and portions are huge.  See you there.

Firstly. From the second you step into this place the customer service is AMAZING. you are greeted by all staff. its hilariously amazing.
The food... unreal. My friends and I ordered a bunch of things off the menu and we all shared (i find this to be the best experience menu wise) 
The oysters covered in cheese.... by far my fav. Don't leave unless you've tried this.
Atmosphere, customer service and food quality all get 5 stars from me.
This is the perfect friends dinner spot or a fun date!

My family relocated to Tempe from Memphis, TN in Sept of last year.  We had a rough relocation and lost the apartment and jobs that we had set up before we got here so we had to start the entire search again. This was the 2nd apartment complex we visited.  The staff was extremely helpful.  The apartments were clean and nice.  We filled out the app the same day and moved in the next day.  The staff is prompt in repairing things that need repairing.  There are children in the neighborhood but they aren't trouble makers.  The landscaping is very well kept.  We would definitely recommend this complex to others.

We had dinner here on an internet deal we found, which put me on edge somewhat considering bargain-priced sushi sounded like a risky idea. However, we were pleasantly surprised by the food. Granted, it isn't world-class sushi and somewhat nontraditional in its composition, but it tasted good and fresh, nonetheless. The Sunfire Roll is divine and the cheesecake is certainly worth saving room for. 

The service was top-notch. Our waiter brought us soup on the house, and even went as far as telling us the food from the internet deal could feed our cast of four, thus not requiring us to spend money unnecessarily on more. However, there were two who didn't eat seafood, so they ordered chicken dishes for themselves, which they thoroughly enjoyed. 

Located in Planet Hollywood, the ambiance is modern and swanky with comfortable seating. The atmosphere is on the darker side but well-suited for conversation over one of their many options for beer, wine, and sake. Just be prepared to pay Vegas strip prices on libations. This standard tends to madden other reviewers, but if you're aware ahead of time, it might save you some sticker shock. Overall, it's definitely worth dropping by for some good food and service in a nice setting.

Mr. Robinson you keep bringing up the point that a credit was put on our account and how nice you were to do that. The fact of the matter is that your company made a promise to me you did not keep and that was a good gesture of customer service to fix it. If the property could not be ready I should have been told that from the beginning so I could find another one. When we moved in, there was damaged appliances, backed up plumbing, and your paint guys painted over already damaged walls that you chose to blame on me. The spa cover was requested to cover the broken spa you ended up charging me to fix that didn't work in the first place that we were told it was going to be removed. I tried to show pictures and explain these points to your company and I was told tough luck. You and your company stole from me in the end. From the look of the other reviews you do this to many other people as well. Hopefully my review will save at least one person from having the same rotten experience I did.
I never go in, I only ever call in for take out.  It's decent food, sometimes the wait is a little long, but decent for a chain.

Never got our bread.  Steaks were ok.  Mac was truffle overboard.  Steak tartar bland.  Lobster bisque was good just ask to add some Chardonnay to bring out more of the flavor.  Also they pushed us out at close when enjoying our wine.  Not acceptable.

great place. got to get their early on their wine and prosciutto special night to get a decent seat. it gets crowded and a bit loud at times but the atmosphere is still nice for hanging out or even a date night. good location to walk old town gilbert while waiting for a table if you show up later.

Magic without the illusions. Never before have I walked out of a barbershop with a smile on my face.

There was a long wait, which was down to how meticulous Valentino is with each customer - but the wait was well worth it. He knew exactly what I was looking for without me having to say much, he spends a good amount of time on the haircut using his machine, scissors and razor as needed. Most places will be happy to do a quick job and let you go in 10 minutes. Here, however, he spends a good 25-30 minutes on your haircut, making sure you have just the look you were hoping for. I saw people before me who were getting their haircut, and he made everyone look sharp, regardless of hair type or age.

Right before I left, he asked me, "See you again?" and I gave him the only appropriate response: "Definitely."

Fantastic food! 

Everything we ordered was delicious - I can't wait to go back. 

The service was also amazing!

Bagel was good. But SOOOOO slow.

I came in Sunday morning at 850 am, I walked right up to the counter to order & was thinking "wow that was quick" but then I noticed there were like 6 people waiting for their food. I noticed two people in the back making the orders one would like take a break and get water. Then there were two cashiers just hanging out doing not much. 

Maybe make this process more efficient Einstein's?? Like Starbucks, the cashiers also help make the food? (Supply Chain Major here -- efficiency is key!!)

I would only eat here if I was saving my own life - and even then I would be selective. This place is grungy and dirty, needs an overhaul or maybe take it out altogether? 
The bartender needs to find a new gig. Slow, uncaring, not helpful.
We went in for a mid-day drink (we were staying at TI)  - we had a 2 for 1 drink coupon which is a joke as they are so expensive anyways for what you get. My mom thought her marg was too sweet and did not drink it. 
Mine was on the rocks so a little better - not much - but I felt like it was such a HUGE favor to ask our lovely bartender for extra ice. Why do I keep tipping for crap service?
Check the bar out and how gross/filthy the in-bar slot machines are. You may want to go elsewhere for food and drink!

LOVED this place! Loved the food, loved the ambiance, loved the drinks, loved just about everything!

-1 star for the waistresses. They are quite the snobby type.

Other than our waitress, the food is great and so are the drinks. I thoroughly enjoyed their pink tacos! You could imagine my disappointment when I completely forgot I wouldn't be able to reheat my leftovers in the hotel room :(

I love this place! I went in today for the first time,  got a 20% off discount because it was my first time and I ended up having Kaitlyn! She was awesome, she's hand paints all her art from a pretty butterfly to Audrey Hepburn ! She's freakin' amazing! The atmosphere is nice, very energetic and friendly. I love love LOVE it  its amazing! I hands down recommend it!!
Food was great...the service was the BEST ever...most personable and charming server we've ever had.....GREAT dining experience
Decent place to get your Chinese food fix if you live closeby and don't want to go too far.    Food is alright.  The walls can use a new coat of paint to make the place look less dirty/dated.

ATT has rounded Direct TV. their  new guide is have soft ware problems. they no longer support called ID because people do dot have land lines THIS is NOT True. Every month my bill is higher for the lace of quality pictures, freezes, slow changing channels on older boxes lack of support. On one of my receivers after I turn it on with the remote  I get no signal, I need to press center power button to shut off box the press again to get a picture. This have gone on science December.

Switch to COX

Perfect place to get a quick fix! I got a ring guard on my engagement ring until I could get it resized. 5 min fix & $10 later perfect!! 

They are awesome!!!

We are just passing through from the East Coast. Charleston, Sc to be exact. 

We have some of the best chefs and dining in the country. Looking up something close on Yelp i found this gem. The reviews were excellent. We decided to try it and all i can say is wow. 

I had the carne asada plate and  it was outstanding.  The wife had fresco max  taco, a big slice of avocado on it. The chips and salsa were a welcome treat as well. 

The owner takes pride in his place and the food he serves. Don't pass this place by.

Delicious food both from the dim sum cart and from the menu. The service was extremely fast as well. The music was louder than I'd like for a dinner atmosphere, making it harder to hear our conversations. I'd still go back if I'm ever around.

First time to try the sister restaurant of Alla Famiglia...a friend suggested it because we were in Southpointe. The building....awesome, a turn-of-the-century schoolhouse. The bar...second floor walk up, cozy, friendly and very comfortable. The restaurant...love it...great space, open and airy, tables not crammed one on top of the next. The food is very good. We started with the smoked provolone and the bruschetta. The smoked provolone is sublime. I chose the veal Milanese which is a double chop pounded thin and sautéed with pine nuts, lump crab meat and some tart lemon...this is huge and so tender you can almost cut it with your fork. The crab is fresh and compliments the lightly breaded veal...sort of a twist on surf and turf. My dining companion chose the filet with Gorgonzola cream, also very flavorful and perfectly cooked...medium well...just like she ordered it ( a travesty in my opinion but then I wasn't eating it!). The house salad and the fusilli pasta w/ vodka sauce are both good. The salad has roasted beets which makes it delicious in my book! Ignore the naysayers and the tightwads...this place is worth every penny...I'll be back!

If there were 6 stars that is what I would have chosen! Chance and his entire staff are extremely professional and knowledgeable. I had many questions and concerns regarding the maintenance and care of my lawn and he addressed every concern and always went the extra mile to help. I will never use another landscaper! I have been spoiled! Oh...and the prices are very reasonable.

What a great experience!! Absolutely appreciate the honesty and service from the moment I walked in the door!! If your looking for a fantastic experience, you have to come and see Dr. Gelo and his amazing staff!!

Ok, I've waited 2 days to post this to hopefully get my anger to not show across this review. I chose this store do to the customer service in the past. They are probably the best in the far East valley. BUT, I went in on Thursday with a software issue on my phone, to the point I could not use my phone which is my money maker. The guy started off good, but things turned quickly. He immediately decided I needed a new phone. I'm out of warranty and do not have insurance on it. I'm passed due on my bill and couldn't make the payment till the next day. He was no help what so ever and I tore out of there in a heaping rage. I called Verizon from my wife's phone and was given the best person out there. She knew what was wrong and went through all the steps to correct the failed software update without sending me a new phone. All this guy at the shop had to do was look into the issue, but no he wanted me to pay more and wait 2 days for a new phone. It's not that I won't go back to the store, because I will to see new products, but I will not but anything in store ever again. I will take my time online and order or call and order. I'm sorry, but it seems that customer service in all Verizon stores does not exist.

This is the place to go if you want to get pregnant and have obstacles. I felt more hopeful and positive than I have in a long time. Dr. Shapiro and staff were friendly and very helpful. The treatment we are getting is aggressive. By that I mean they want to do as much to help you, as soon as they can. We have limited time due to age. They order and explain the diagnostics so you don't feel so confused or afraid. They extend personal lines of communication to help you with your journey. My husband and I have just started our care with Dr. Shapiro but, I finally feel like we are going in the right direction with the right people.

I am a picky eater from Asia but the food at Alihan's is fresh and delicious! Service is friendly and fast, very courteous and makes you feel taken care of. Alihan, the owner is always there making sure everything is tip-top. The interior is very modern, everything is very clean! They have beautiful silverware and other things that are gorgeous hand made and shipped from Turkey. Alex is awesome, and Alihan's girlfriend who works there as manager  is so nice!  We dined there 4 times within 3 days we stayed in Pittsburgh , one day we had 2 dinners there ) and everything was consistently great!
 Did I mention that the prices are very reasonable ? Dinner for two under $50 with drinks and dessert!

Our family is a huge fan of Pin Kaow.  We were going to try Prommares, but instead chose Archi's.  

Food - I had the Tofu Pad Thai (spicy level 6) and Vegetable Fried Rice.  The Pad Thai was ok.  I wasn't blown away from it and wasn't left wanting more.  I asked the server to fry the Tofu crisp and it came out soft.  They should have fried it a little bit longer.  The spice level was appropriate and enjoyable.  I felt the same way about the Fried Rice.  It was just ok.

Atmosphere - The restaurant is small and the tables kind of feel on top of each other.  We prefer a more private dining experience.  We had a party of 6 people and that is probably the most I'd try to take here.  There is enough room to get larger groups in there, but it wouldn't feel comfortable in my opinion.

Service - The service was good.  The servers were friendly.

Will I return?  Probably not.....unless I'm invited there by a friend or family member.

Came here after a long day at the NPC North American Championships (bodybuilding competition) as a triple date.  All three couples got the chateaubriand for two along with a variety or appetizers and different desserts.

The ambiance, food and service are AMAZING!  I am definitely a fan.  The place is upscale and formal, so lean towards the side of caution and dress either dress casual or formal with a jacket.  The venue is beautifully decorated with a stellar view both inside and outside of Pittsburgh.  There was a live band the night my partner and I were there with friends.  As per the food, from the appetizers to dessert, everything was perfect and down to the dot!  The serving size for appetizers are fair and entrees are generous.

For anyone seeking an intimate night with a loved one, Le Mont is definitely a place to consider.

Impressive tap room for the selection and the size of the place. Food was good, in particular the burger which was juicy, flavorful and not overloaded. Classic. Very good fries too, and generous servings. Two admittedly persnickety criticisms: the lime guacamole was, er, too limey. I mean, they did warn us by calling it "Lime guacamole" but I prefer the garlicky variety with a hint of lime, not the inverse. My dining companion liked the guacamole just fine. The tap list was too skewed to local Ontario selections. Good on them I guess for supporting local businesses but I think the microbrew thing has gone too far and affects the quality of selection. Would have liked to see more European selections. But they did have Delerium Tremens, which is a solid Belgian. Friendly and attentive service.

Beautiful decor. Well thought out, open kitchen, with considered, consistent theme throughout restaurant and outside seating area. Started with the salmon appetizer, and though had high expectations, was still blown away.  Main was the Korean skirt steak; incredible.  Coffee at end of meal also on point.  Varied menu with lots of interesting choices, as well as accommodating chefs for those in party with quite strict dietary requirements.  Highly recommend.

The restaurant week dinner option was great. We had fondue, vodka pasta and bananas foster as a 3 course meal. The ambiance here is cool and classy. Like a speak easy. It feels very unique for Phoenix. 
The only complaint is that our server over charged us almost $50 on our bill. It was quickly corrected.

I called to see how much they sell their Quest bars for so I would know if it was worth the trip or not, and she refused to give me a price over the phone, but assured me they have all the flavors. I decided to risk it & go anyway, and when I got there, I was shocked to see they are $2.49/bar! They also only sold maybe 5-7 flavors individually, otherwise you had to buy an entire box. When I checked out, she wouldn't even let me use my credit card since I wasn't making a $10 purchase, which is actually a legal violation of the contract stores have with credit card carriers. I do not recommend this place!!
Some of my favorite, affordably priced and super tasty Greek food in the city! The Gyro, Chicken and Tzatziki are so delicious. The house wine is affordable and wonderful too.
First Chicken Shwarma, best so far.  Good place.I found it on the run and couldn't have been more satisfied.

What a joke! Can I get a ZERO stars option? This was our 2nd time dining here and OMG what difference a few months has made! This was one of the worst dinners I have had in a long time. HORRIBLE service!!!!!You would think this is a self serve restaurant. Sat down never got our drinks till we asked for it...Empty in there, No excuse. The little service you do receive is very poor and they all seem more interested in hanging out and talking to each other behind the cashier. Absolutely no attention.
I was hoping that the food would make up for the horrible service.
The fish was not fresh, it looked like it was left out in the open for awhile all dehydrated, got FOOD POISONING!!!! as a result of our visit, we were completely incapacitated for the following 24 hours. Reporting to Southern Nevada Health District, you've been warned.
No wonder they have to lie to the public by saying its there "Renew"? Raised the prices and reduced the size, I guess that should have been a sign. 

Overall, I would not be back, there are so many good sushi restaurants and IZAKAYA in Vegas to settle for this one. Not worth the money at all and over priced at that! UGH!!!!

My boyfriend took me to Roka Akor for my birthday this year, and I have never been there before. I love it! i liked how the restaurant was decorated, all the staff was very nice and approachable, and have some of the freshest sashimi! The first time I came here, they brought us the sushi of the day, and with fresh sea salt which they freshly scraped off this huge rock, that was very cool. everything was cooked right. i got the lamb cutlets, the meat fell perfectly off the bone. was delicious. the service was outstanding. I have no complaints.

now they have happy hour from 5-close we always stop and grab some saki or even a saki-sangria or two :)
Service was bad, food was good. It took 5 minutes for the hostess to acknowledge my girlfriend and I. The server was slow and rarely seen.

The food is great, the service not so much. They recently changed what used to be a QSR type restaurant to a "sit down and have a waitress serve and expect a tip" type place unless you dine out. It does seem the time it takes for your food to come out is longer than any other place I've been too. Also, if you are only "ordering out" you cannot sit at a table to wait, you must stand awkwardly in the corner waiting for your food to come out eventually. The homemade gluten free bread and deserts are amazing though.

Don't get me wrong, the food at the Canaletto was magnificent. Italian at its best with a beautiful view of the main square.
HOWEVER,
the service was deplorable. When my family and I got there, we were treated poorly by the seater.  We had requested an OPEN table next to the street for a better experience. She curtly told us that it was saved for someone at that exact moment and that we would have to sit at very poor seats or wait 20 minutes... for an OPEN table. Then, when we asked for the manager, she snipes, "Me and him are both the same so you don't have to talk to him."  

Then when we finally got the table, it takes 10 more minutes to get a waiter. Of course, once the manager noticed us, everything was peachy. It should not have taken us 30+ minutes to even get water to drink for a restaurant that tries to be high class.

I have mixed feelings about Crave. I absolutely love their ambience. I have been here a few times on dates and with friends and it is a perfect hangout spot. The music is never too loud to not be able to hear your company and I enjoyed the dim-lights and the comfy couches. The hookah is what sells this place for me because their desserts are sub-par at best. I had better cheesecake at Ruby's Tuesday and that's saying a lot. Maybe I am just bougie but I bake myself and their desserts just did not do it for me. So if you are looking for a nice place for a date/hookah, Crave is the place for you but certainly not for their desserts.

Thanks Wade for the awesome service you provided me! I called around 5 other places and never got a definitive answer on cost or time. Calling you was as simple as it gets. You provided me with all the answers on the spot and made the experience enjoyable and I love the new exhaust on my truck. My fathers truck is next so I'll be stopping by again soon! Thank you again Wade!!

Banh Mi Boys is a safe go to spot for quick eats. No frills order your food and they'll call you when it's ready. It's always busy so expect a line up. 

We discovered the Club Bao (pork belly + chicken) and have never looked back - you can also do the club Banh Mi style as well. Kimchi fries are great for sharing  comes topped up with kimchi and pulled pork. Habaneros on the side.

We stayed over in Henderson for one night. As soon as we checked in the Hampton Inn, noticed the Sunset Palace next door (didn't stay there because I know about there "extra" fees). We went to the Grand Cafe for dinner and then the next morning had breakfast there before leaving town. We had wonderful service and enjoyed our waitresses. The food was very good. Had to help my husband eat his enormous stack of tasty pancakes.
Will eat here again when in town.
friendly staff, awesome vintage cars in the showroom, I've been to a lot of VW dealers all over the southwest, this is definitely one of my favorites!
No Frills brand Chicken Nuggets passed off as "boneless wings" are you kidding me? The pizza itself was fine but the nuggets and my half full box of wedges made this a terrible experience.

I really enjoy this salon. The staff is always so friendly and accommodating, especially the females in the shop. Although I have only gotten pedicures here, they seem extremely talented with manicures and keeping up on new trends. They don't try to up-sale you on services. It's all around a great salon.

Not happy today! I come to this casino often and have spent way too much money. Today I was looking forward to playing the Black Diamond machine that was up to $50,000.00! A lady sat at that machine just before me. She won $1,500 and then $3,300. After about an hour I noticed casino staff talking with her. They put the machine "Temporarily Out of Service". I overheard them talking about what time she would be returning to the Casino. I waited 3 hours for this machine. The lady returned to the Casino and immediately got the machine. I saw them then put it back in service for her. She then won another $1800.00! Why would I ever return to this casino!!

Actually rating on this place was not so good but then I realized  not was done by a chinese. Shanghai cuisine is quite unique and has a different taste yo most chinese food. I try to avoid it but still like it.
Today the rabbit was really good. Don't think it was shanghaineese but i liked it. So was the bambo and spice lotus. Beef soup was more of a thai style and of course the Xiao long bap both steamed and fried were excellent. 
Since my wife is from Shanghai I have a feeling we will be back here.
Walking away after standing at the hostess station for 3 mins while being stared at by the kitchen staff and not seated or acknowledged.   Guess they don't want our business.

Alexis helped me with my new contact lenses. She was great, patient, and offered me coupons. I was recommended this place by a friend and very pleased. Dr. Rist didn't have much of a personality, very straight forward and to point.

This store is clean and  good in general, lot of Asian or Chinese products but my main concern is HALAL Food which I don't feel comfortable to buy from this store as they are selling Pork and many products with "Haram"  Ingredients,  handing of food is good,

This place is great. The staff was very welcoming the first time I came in to buy some crickets for my bearded dragon. Very knowledgeable when it comes to reptiles. They have great deals and I will definitely be a regular at this store.

Thanks for the business.

Quirky, weird bar with interesting props and things to keep you entertained. I thought the Spin the Wheel thing was fun (3 shots for 7 dollars). It is very dive-y and makes you feel kind of gross after you leave the place. Kind of an older crowd...don't know if I would ever go out of  my way to come back here.

Customer service is poor, but the donuts are the best! I love that they are open 24 hours. I start work at 4:30 AM so it's helpful I can count on Bosa for a sweet tooth craving any time of the day. The glazed donuts are my favorite. Keep it simple :)

Met some friends for breakfast here and was very impressed with their quiche. It comes with a small cup of aioli, which is totally not needed, and a small, perfectly composed side salad. The quiche was possibly the most fluffy and soft quiche I've ever eaten. That day, they had turnips and parsnips in there and while those were not my fave veggies, it worked with the quiche. I don't know how they get it that fluffy. Butter? Or sorcery? The crust was also very tender and flaky. Best crust ever. The side salad was a perfect foil to the richness of the egg pie.

These guys do a great job with great customer service! They were able to get some stains out of the seats I had thought would be permanent. Dylan and Anna always make you feel welcome and are very appreciative of to have your business. A bit expensive, but excellent work. Highly recommended!!!

I love the food at this place! I actually love alot of things about this place. The only thing is that it can be expensive without you even realizing untill you get the bill. My advice... go for 1/2 price tapas at happy hour! Gazpacho is my favorite only $5. They have this crab stuffed pepper that is to die for.

I have purchased several vehicles from this company.  Prior to my first purchase I was leery as this is a small business compared to the huge ones on Bell Rd.  However, they had a nice assortment of vehicles and mechanically and visibly this small dealer seems to want to present a quality used vehicle.  Their prices are about the same as the larger dealers and certainly higher than Craigs list but Auto Paradise has checked the vehicles  over and their mechanic is very competent.  Rocky and Brett, the salesmen, are personable with no high pressure.
Great customer service and employees who really care. I highly recommend this firm! The years of experience they have and the sincere compassion they offer is really wonderful.
No service unless asked for, and even then we weren't really 'served', just sort of ignored. Never going there again.

Drove across town to get to this place and what a massive disappointment. I called before coming to make sure they could meet my request which they made it sound like they could. When I walked in I worked with the guy I spoke with on the phone. He told me several times, "I'm sorry, I don't follow" when my directions were very clear and written out on a piece of paper. In addition he told me I'd have to come back when the owner was there because he just wasn't sure if they could do it. After telling him what kind of carpet I wanted, he started showing me all different color and sizes. Very odd. Won't be back.

This is the best poke shop I've eaten at in Arizona. I asked the owner about it, he used to be a sushi chef for many years, and only buys the top quality fish and personally inspects each delivery, rejecting any fish that doesn't meet his standards. That must be why I enjoy eating here every time, that and the fresh cucumber, crab, ginger and other add-ons and sauce I add to my order. This is one of those word-of-mouth places you have to try because you won't see tons of ads all over town. It's hard to find good tasting fish in Arizona, but this place has it.
