5 starts for 5 star service from the best bartender out there! Shout out to Lori for always rockin it! She's the only reason I come. And the good food. Stacy is the best cook here.

It was a good late night spot to grab and quick and easy pizza. It had some good ingredients and was definitely worth the trip. I noticed that several reviews stated that the water dispenser was broken. It was not dispensing water for the longest possible time (15 minutes almost). Forced me to buy a bottle of water for 4.5 dollars. The staff didn't bother help fix or provide an alternate source even after repeated requests. Recommended for the pizza only.

I would only come here for the fries.

The chicken cheesesteak (yes, my standards are high since I'm from Philly) was so bland. The bread was porous and too big for the small amount of unseasoned chicken. I probably ate like 300 calories worth of hot sauce of ketchup to make up for it. And I think there was cheese- if it was there, I didn't taste it.

The regular and sweet potato fries are awesome. Besides that, the subs are not worth your calories. Well, at least the price was right.

Brunch was fannnnntastic. Took a 15 year old, sat on the patio and went to town w the menu. $45 did iced coffee, thick cut, fatty bacon and citrus donut holes, just piled it all onto one plate and amazing. Go for it. Then we got the chile verde breakfast burrito and the chicken n waffles (red velvet waffles, might I add) and just devoured them between the two of us. Honestly enough food for three. Everything tasted fantastic and the timing was great, even on a Saturday morning we didn't have to wait more than 15 for everything. They also make French toasts and bennies, but we couldn't make enough room to try more so we made a reservation for tomorrow morning. The lox looked great, too. Our server was Brittney and she was a delight. She had my 15 year old saying things like "you're the best server we've ever had," and making promises to bring his girlfriend back. So cute. I'm glad we went for the recommendations and you should too. Ask for Brit.

I had twice as much to say! But the app wouldn't let me put it all down... This is a condensed version, LOL if you can call it that. 
For those of you that know me, let's talk parking! You all know parking is super important for so many reasons to me.... mainly safety!! This place is an absolute nightmare. No valet!, The parking lot and surrounding areas to park is not safe at all!!! My rental car actually had its plates stolen the last time I stayed here!!! Dark parking garage, min parking around the building, busses coming in and out where a person should park to check in!!! Nightmare!! That's the kind of place were talking about folks!!  And it has gotten worse from the last time he stayed here about six months ago.
I arrive it's around 10:30 on a Monday night I'm exhausted ... The staff was not friendly.... Two bottles of water here's your floor... Even though I happened to be a very nice level within the Hilton honors membership!... 
I get to my room, BOOM!! Right at the gate, the smell of sewage coming out of the bathroom is almost unbearable! I immediately close the sink drain, the bathroom drain and the one vent in the bathroom! And closed the door!  It did help a little bit. I called the front desk to tell them about the horrid smell and leaking bathtub coming from the bathroom, As you can see below, And they said they would have someone up....I waited literally an hour and 15 minutes, then called - they said they are on lunch and will come up
After,  it's 9:10 PM!!!!! The "engineer comes up to say... what happened to the toilet.... I seriously thought I was going to pee myself laughing so hard! He drained the tub and then told me.... the leaking has been fixed but I don't smell the smell, I can give you a SPRAY! nothing we can do! He gave me a card that said 24/7!! haaaaaaaaaaaaaa only when your not on BREAK! He left the drain open AND LEAVE THE DRAIN OPEN AND a WIERD PILLOW CASE ON THE TOILET! ( see below! ) Like maybe that is what he used to open the drain!... I did not even see him bring that in with him!! Like maybe he had his pocket? So weird! So weird so weird so weird so weird!! I'm serious folks! I can't make this stuff up!! Ha!!!!!!!!!!!Oh my gray! Ok you get the point, I was super irritated. Moving on! 
There were un matched paint touchups throughout the entire room, big bold anchor nail holes in the wall with off-color dirty marks around the frame... WITHOUT THE FRAME!! Not to mention the disgusting horrible stains on the beautiful bench directly to the left of the TV... At the foot of your bed! ( see below! ) 
The Wi-Fi here is totally a joke! It's very very spotty to say the least have to check in every single day... it drops the signal on the 30 min mark... almost to the dot, They don't have an option for a wifi check in for your entire stay....,just another inconvenience.  
At this point it will never stay at this hotel again... As I said the last time that my plates got stolen! However, as all of you know, I would give them another try for the benefit of the doubt! Bad bad bad decision!
Let's talk about the good for 2.5 seconds, there is a hairdryer in the bathroom there is a bar downstairs... That actually does have pretty decent Pinot Grigio wine,  that in itself! Gave them the second star... I'm just saying, not to mention the bartender here is absolutely amazing super friendly love her love her love her! and it's right off the strip. The air-conditioner and small  refrigerator works really well. I didn't try to TV because I will never ever touch and hotel remote control in my life !!! 
The food is average breakfast hotel food, nothing fresh... But you know what I'm saying. The cups are about the size of a children's Starbucks, so not a grande... But below that. It's the only size they offer... And it's bold regular or decaf. They don't offer sugar in The raw...being super picky at this point, however they do offer half and half regular milk... And the big pump things full of French vanilla and hazelnut creamer, The non-refrigerated kind. I no some people love that, however not my thing.
I never ever get housekeeping, so I really can't comment on that.
There is plenty of space in the drawers, easy to open and the sliding mechanisms are obviously taken care of.And the bed is super comfortable. The duvet however, is a nightmare! There's the scratchy thing on top and a smooth piece on the bottom, however your duvet is always going to touch your face! So you have to pull your sheet way up over your head so that the sheet touches your face and not The scratchy duvet cover! I don't like that!!, I bring my own blanket with me sometimes, thank God this is one of those times.

Lots and lots of family and children here... Again not really my thing.  You be the judge. 

Update, while checking out I told him about my experience. They explained they are going to begin renovations soon and comped me a full night! It was the right thing to do.

I've been going here for two years now. They always ask you if you want water, tea, coffee when getting settled. I always get my haircut done by Andrea and I love her, she never disappoints. She makes sure to listen to what you want, looks carefully at pictures you give her (if you do), asks you about what kind of styling you do to your hair (blow dry/air dry, curl, straighten, etc), and a lot of more nice stuff. She really listens. If you plan on colouring your hair but aren't sure of what to do yet or have an idea but need a professional's opinion, you can also ask her because she also seems to have knowledge on what would be good for your hair when it comes to colour. 

For colouring though, I go to Damon. I've been to him once, and from that first time, it's safe to say that I will definitely go back to him whenever I will want to colour my hair. I had an appointment with him the day after I got a haircut from Andrea and she told him what I wanted, they pretty much explained to me the same thing of what the results/process of colouring my hair would be (because it's long and thick). Damon did a great job at fixing my already coloured hair (with ugly grown out roots). He was so sweet, making sure I was comfortable. I had a friend with me, so I wasn't bored while waiting for my colour to set and Damon joined in our conversation like we were friends for a long time. A slight problem that I had after getting my hair rinsed was that I had to schedule an appointment for blow drying because it is not provided with the colouring (you have to pay for the blow drying separately). I found it silly, but it was okay. At the end of my appointment, my hair looked great & felt great (still feels great) even after being coloured.

All I have to say is, I would highly recommend going Adikt Salon for a haircut and for colouring. :)

AWFUL!!!  BJ'S ON CHARLESTON IN VEGAS

I'm in vegas on vacation (here for a month)  and this  visit to BJ's was  an  EPIC FAIL!!!  
My party consisted of two, we were seated, I ordered a cappuccino and it was delicious and hot upon arrival, however  my food arrived cold and I told my server 3 times that I have allergies (I carry an Epipen). 
I ordered the turkey burger with NO Avocado, NO Tomatoes and NO Cranberries and my friend ordered  a different burger.  My order came with EXTRA Cranberries, Cold french fries and my friends burger was cold along with Cold french fries as well, When we flagged down the server,  and told him about our order, he offered to take it back to the kitchen but due to fear and bad experiences with the food being returned we declined and LEFT!  
The server didn't offer any type of discount or condolences for our loss of appetite and acted as if his mind was on other things, possibly day dreaming of another job etc.   So a waste of $40 and we ended up going somewhere else for Lunch AGAIN as replacement for the food purchased at BJ's.  THIS IS TERRIBLE!!!   

Management needs to take these complaints seriously, if this keeps up this restaurant will have to be shut down for good for lack of business!!

Since I've gotten on this breakfast in the afternoon kick and Mickey ds has the breakfast burritos which are like a dollar each. This is an awesome solution for breakfast if you're looking for a quick bite to eat and you know I spent any money. You can also grab the breakfast egg McMuffin that's a couple bucks but super tasty as well I normally just take off one of the pieces of the funds since that's where you get a lot of your carbs at. Also this location is nice because you can hop right back up on the freeway either way either to downtown Las Vegas or back to Los Angeles.

Best miso soup I have ever had. The maki was enjoyable and unique, with interesting combinations. The maki is really fat compared to most places I've had. Pricing was reasonable and the service was great even though they were very busy. Staff was all really friendly. They do not serve alcohol.

My wife and I usually go out to eat on Sundays when Buon Gusto is closed so we made a point to go there Saturday and finally try it. The service is great, a very friendly staff that make you feel at home. My wife ordered the Broccoli Penne and I ordered the Buon Gusto. My wife's Broccoli Penne was great no complaints, the Buon gusto however was just a little better than average which was kind of surprising since its named after the place. For desert we tried the bread pudding which is 6 out of 5 stars. I would give this place 4.5 out of 5 stars but thats not an option so well go with 5.

I came here as I received a birthday coupon for a free entree as I would frequently visit the Rubio's at Monte Carlo as I worked at ARIA.  While I was impressed by the gentleman's professionalism and wishing me a happy birthday, the food was mediocre.  I ordered a shrimp quesadilla and there was substantially less shrimp in my quesadilla then there typically is at the location at Monte Carlo.  Disappointing for the food but excellent service!

While in town we where in the mood for some pizza and pasta. This place is not far from the strip and very inexpensive. They have great deals to take advantage from individually or for families. Pizza was great and Alfredo pasta . Staff is very friendly. Location is easy to find. Would love to stop by again when in town.

I want to think that Rolled Ice Cream is something amazing, but I just don't get the allure. Maybe I'm becoming some some cranky old mid-30yo, but it just didn't work for me.

First, the line. It's like this place was giving away free Rolex's. They weren't. So waiting 20-25 minutes in line was a bad start. 

Second, the process. They have a bunch of ice cream making stations. The way they do the ice cream, pouring it out fresh, is cool, I'll give them that. But then it's a bunch of chopping and slicing and dicing, picking ingredients, then more slicing and dicing, eventually leading to the ultimate build up of rolling the ice cream and serving. 

Third, the final product. Eh. I mean it's ice cream. I got a traditional mix in of Reeses Peanut Butter Cups. My wife got a Ding Dong & chocolate syrup mixed in. It just wasn't that good. Maybe candy isn't what it used to be? The chocolate became super waxy and just stuck to our teeth. You could hardly taste the chocolate syrup that was added. The presentation was nice, but after the second or third bite you're no longer eating "rolled ice cream" you're eating a cup of ice cream. 

I'd rather have Thrifty Ice Cream or Baskin Robbins. If I'm in the mood for a mix in, the classic Cold Stone would do the trick. 

Maybe I'm getting old. Maybe it just wasn't that good. Not sure which, but rolled ice cream just doesn't excite me.

I've been to this place a number of times, as I always seem to confuse the name with the Good Egg and expect the same goodness. Never do I find it.

This last visit will be the absolute last. We sat down, waited 5min to even be acknowledged and she took our drink orders. 15min later, the drinks came, and she barely remembered to ask for our food orders. We asked for water then too. An hour later (literally), we get a jug of water, no glasses. Another 10min for glasses. Still no sign of the food.

Stayed for 4 days. 
Very nice staff specially Abraham (the Filipino gentleman).
Breakfast is good. Tasty compare to other usual breakfast in other hotel.
We enjoyed the pool, its a little cold and no clock though.
We had a King suite - it fits 3 adults, 2 toddlers and a baby. We had the bed, pull out couch, rollaway bed and a crib. 
The set up of the room is a little bit off though. No dining table on a suite but there is a huge office table separating the bedroom and the living room. Mirror and sink are outside the bathroom.
There is only 3 small drawers for clothes.

Wow. Shishtawook was better than I could have imagined and the Taboulli is on point. Nothing like Mrs. Chelala's, but none other compares to hers. Plus, taboulli is day to day, could be less fresh tomorrow, so dont read this and go on my experience if yours is not as tasty. Commenting on how the "Yelps' Bruce Lee-Roy" Steve L. Was wrong about taboulli, I dont wanna hear it. 

I have had this place in my radar for quite some time now, im in no way disappointed, im actually thinking about what I will order next time..? 

Could not have had a better 300th review!

update, I had this in my draft, it was to my 300, still an excellent place and review!

This place is surprisingly nice on the inside and has a wide array of menu options.

This is not just another ***bertos it is a hybrid seat down place.

You sit, get a menu that's not on the wall, and then order to a person at your table.  The menu if full of great options from traditional plates and Mexican fare like burritos and tacos, to less seen in the gringo world real gorditas.

Your meal will start with chips that come with some salsa bean mix on top.  I am not sure if it is veg so be sure to ask them to leave it off if you care. There is a salsa bar with one of the best red salsas I have had in a long time, green salsa, avocado dip, carrots, pico and a crock pot of beans again probably not veg.

Prices are pretty good my chillie rellno plate was on special for $6 a huge plate with rice beans tortillas (corn or flour) and a great large chillie rellno.

Sure this may be a bit west of the trendy down town but it's worth a try.

I found this place while wandering around Scottsdale and I needed a quick lunch. It's a quaint little diner. Service was very friendly and quick. She recommended the flautas as they were her favorite. Glad I took her advice!  Soft shredded chicken in the middle and perfectly crunchy taco on the outside.  Nice serving of guacamole to go with it too.  Loved it as a good in and out place for lunch!

I have gone to this Wendy's since it opened and we have lived in this neighborhood for 31 years.  This store has gotten progressively worse.  Always different help and always different managers.  Guess they can't keep anyone.

They are slow.  When I order a salad, I have to wait 15 to 20 minutes sometimes as they tell me they ran out of grilled chicken.  What!!
This morning we stopped by after church and bought a 4 for 4 for one of the babies and my husband.  He ordered the grilled chicken and it was cold.  I got my other son large french fries and both orders of fries were cold and stale.  We were there around 10:20 am and they don't open until 10am.  I took my order inside and asked for the manger who came from the back and claimed everything was just made fresh.  I told him I didn't think so as the fries were cold and stale and my husband's wrap was cold.  Again, he is arguing with me that everything was made fresh and then told his employees there were only 3 there to get me more french fries and chicken nuggets.  He took the wrap in the back and put it in the microwave.

I never received and I'm sorry just an attitude.  The older woman behind the counter told me she was sorry a couple of times.  I told them all that there was another Wendy's around the corner on Deer Valley and that is where I will be going to from now on.

Now I know why this place doesn't have any customers and will end up with no customers if someone doesn't do something soon.

Report this company to the Better Business Bureau if you want results for billing or refund problems.  That is what I did several years ago and actually got someone's attention who called me and refunded my money!  I am a couponer.  I get tired of having to go to the store to get a newspaper (I am unable to drive), so I thought I would try it again since I got 2 advertisements in the ads in the mailbox the other day that advertised $4.29 a week for 12 months for the Weds. and Sunday papers.  Well ... when you go to the website to sign up, and read the fine print, it's actually $9.95 a month!  They now charge a $4.99 set-up fee for EZ Pay - but EZ Pay is your only choice!  And they charge you extra for "special edition" papers and the front cover price for papers like the Thanksgiving Day paper.  I don't care about the Thanksgiving Day paper - I only want weekly coupons - but you have no choice, you must take whatever paper they want to send you and you HAVE to pay for it!  Guess I'll be going to the store every Sunday as usual :-(
This place is so much fun. The setup is awesome and couldn't ask for better service. The cars are very easy to drive and control.

I love Pita Jungle. I don't live in Phoenix, but I visit often since my family is there. Every time, I go to Pita Jungle. My last visit, I went straight there from the airport. The food is so yummy, it's easy to order healthy, prices are reasonable, and portions are huge. I always have leftovers. The salads are my favorite, but the chicken plate with beans, rice and garlic sauce is also really good. And they have bottomless refills on my favorite drink -- Arnold Palmers. What more could you want? Pita Jungle, please open a San Francisco location!

I had a very positive experience ant NEE on Pecos. The receptionist was pleasant, checked me and my husband in in a timely manner. Dr. Gasson had a patient with a problem that took him some extra attention - he informed us but still saw us soon after our appointment time. He never made us feel rushed. People need to understand that if they have to wait for a doctor the reason is usually that the doctor is giving his patient the time that he will give you.

I absolutely loved my jade facial with Kellee and my awesome massage with Nicole.  I really enjoyed the mask, steam treatment, and the scalp massage that came along with it.  Everything that she put on my face smelled so good and it was so relaxing!  My massage therapist Nicole also went above and beyond what I had expected from a spa enviornment.  She addressed all my needs and really listened to everything that I said.  I was really impressed with the trigger point therapy that she used on my neck and shoulder area.  She also let me pick between 3 different essential oils and I picked the green tea one and it was wonderful.  I enjoyed every minute of it and I felt so rejuvenated.  They have really good rates for local AZ residents and I will be coming back for some more services in the future.

Okay, I wasn't really sure what to expect here as it's not an American style ice cream place. Actually, it's a Mexican style ice cream place. And let me tell you, it was a great experience. 

I loved the pictures all over the walls and behind the counters. That way, even if you don't know how to pronounce things, you can point to pictures like a kid. Being serious though, being that everything is natural, I'll be back for sure. 

I had the Lime popsicle. It was awesome. My wife had the cream and strawberry popsicle. I liked hers better, but they were completely different from each other. I can't wait to try other flavors, not to mention the actual ice cream. 

Nothing was in English, so be prepared for that, but don't let it deter you from trying them out. They are so worth it. I promise you, you will not regret it.

I came in with pictures of what I wanted and was told something similar could be done but that wasn't the case. 

First, I have clear tips with clear acrylic overlay and they don't have clear tips! I didn't find this out until he had already prepared my nails for a fill and removed 2 nails for replacement. No way I could leave at this point, I had no time to go elsewhere!  So now I have 2 nails with regular (not clear) tips! ‍ The fill turned out fine. 

Second, the final nail design was nothing like what I wanted, but he did what he could with what he had. 

They turned out good but due to limited products, no where near my style!  Don't get me wrong, they do 5 star work, I highly recommend them, as long as you like simple nails and designs. 

I don't! I'm from NY, when have you met a NY'er with "simple" nails?!?! Exactly!! Hence, the 3 stars vs. 5!

I have never written a review before and I wish I could give 0 stars. Overall the service was bad and the food didn't justify the long wait. The food took over 30 mins to arrive after the time we ordered. It took 20 min for our server to come and actually take our order. We asked our server (I think his name is Alejandro; tall, dark hair and olive skinned) to change the channel on the tv but he never did even though he said he would update us. When we asked a second time after we got our food if the manager was okay with it, he stuttered out some excuse about the manager being too busy to change a channel. The restaurant had 6 tables inside. We order the tavern burger, a chicken sandwich, and fish tacos but they were out of fish tacos. The patty in the burger was really dry and tough, as was the chicken that wasn't even flattened or prepared to be placed in a sandwich. The fries were pretty good.

Stopped by patio before an Indians game. There's not much service, you need to wait at the bar and get someone's attention. Once we were served however the bartender was very good. We ordered the nachos, nice and crispy but they came with very little taco meat. The salsa and cheese topping or cold, so it didn't do much for the warmth of the meat. 
But it's super convenient to walk to the Indians game. And the staff were very nice.

Just got done processing my third auto loan through One Nevada and these guys are amazing. They actually just refinanced a new car loan from a dealership at a much lower rate. The application and approval process was simple and Margaret Mims who helped us was fantastic. I highly recommend One Nevada for anyone seeking some kind of loan in the Las Vegas Valley

Hier wird ein gutes Hotelbuffet angeboten. Vielseitige Auswahl an Speisen. Geschmacklich sind diese in Ordnung. Dessert / Kuchen wie überall in den USA viel zu süß. 

Durch sehr großen Andrang kommt es zu Wartezeiten für die Tische und bei dem eigentlich recht schnellen und aufmerksamen Service zu Nachlässigkeiten. (Tische nicht sorgfältig abgewischt.)

How do I begin?.....  I'm going to break this into two pieces.  Quality and Planning/Communication.

First the Quality. HHI's team of carpenters, drywall and tile guys are great. I think they are hard workers and their quality is spot on. VERY happy with the work they have done. I would love to manage this team myself because I feel that under the proper direction, this would be a great team. We did a master bath remodel (complete gut) and they installed a new (larger) shower including curb, retiled floor, shower/vanity wall and tub surround. Awesome work and it turned out beautiful.

Planning/communication. I should state that I have very high expectations. When you tell me something, I hold you to it.  I think HHI is a good company to hire if you don't have deadlines and don't mind micro-managing every step.  The first project manager I was given (yes, I had two), was completely unresponsive. Didn't answer texts or calls. In fact, I have cameras installed in my home and I called him while he was there. He looked at his phone and put it back in his pocket.  In HHI's defense, they let him go so I'll give them that, but before they did, he admitted the company was horrible at communication. 

We specified that we wanted 1/8" grout on the floor and 3/8" on the walls.  We got 1/8" on floor and walls because no one told the tile guys actually doing the work. We didn't bother pushing because it looked ok so we let it go. 

We clearly spelled out that we wanted a 36" shower door. They built the shower curb in such a way that two pieces of glass were needed and a smaller door was required. This was unacceptable because we specifically called out a single piece door. The salesman openly admitted to making the error on the design, but because I didn't catch it, I had to pay an extra $120 to fix their mistake. When I asked the project manager about it, his response was "It was built per the design". Buyer beware. Review your design VERY carefully. If you sign it, it's your fault, no matter how badly they screw up.  

Specifically asked that the shower head be raised 3 inches.  When the plumber showed up, no one had told him. Luckily, I was there at the time and made sure he knew to do it. 

HHI has a very cool online tool with schedules, places for notes, pictures, etc.  Don't bother. They don't read the notes. After making two requests on the notes, neither was read so I left a third note asking if anyone actually reads the notes and to call me immediately. No call. No one reads the notes.  

Last item, the shower glass. This is the last item on the project. I was told that they now do their own shower glass (I was going to go with someone else, originally). They quoted a comparable price and a faster turn-around of roughly 5 biz days.  Glass was measured on Nov. 1st. On the 10th I got a text from the new Project manager telling me the glass was on backorder. They didn't even know about this until it didn't show up on the truck the day it was due. Although not directly their fault, customers don't care about a supplier's sub-supplier. If you commit, you own it. Don't push the blame to the sub-supplier.  Backordered part was finally done and was due in Phoenix Friday morning (11/17) from CA. On Thursday 11/16, I received a text message from the new project manager with a picture attached. The picture was of a pile of shattered tempered glass. No explanation, no message. I didn't want to play "guess what this is" so I called. They told me that the supplier was loading it on the truck and one of the pieces shattered. Now they are rushing to get the glass complete and installed before Thanksgiving. I have guests coming from out of town and don't want 7 of us sharing one small bathroom. I could go on, but won't. This is sufficient. 

Bottom line, the quality of the work (once it's done) is beautiful. The guys in the trenches to great work. If I were rating them on Quality/Workmanship alone, I would have given them a 4 or even a 5.
If you are retired or have lots of time to oversee their work and manage the project for them, I would say go for it. BUT... If you are a working couple like my wife and I, plan on weeks of frustration as you try to get answers to questions. Much of the end result was due to us watching on camera or coming home and inspecting every night and then calling/texting to make sure things were done as planned.

I believe their shortcoming is due to a lack of communication/mgmt. and I believe this is a tops-down issue. Much of my texts and conversations were with Brandon (one of the owners) who was very quick to blame his sub-supplier (for the glass) and say there's nothing they can do. As I said before, customers don't care. As a manager of suppliers, I understand the difficulty he deals with. But I also know that you have to hold your sub-suppliers accountable and MAKE them commit. Drive them to fix problems. Not just say "there's nothing I can do".

OMG, I looooovvveee their gluten free brownies here. They taste just like regular brownies. Their vegan brownies are good, but the gluten free brownies are a perfect creation. 

I had their hotdog buns which I didn't really like at all and ended up throwing them away. 

Their grilled cheese that you can order from their menu is yummy.
Currently my favorite ramen place. When it's busy the wait can be a little long. Otherwise, great food, good service. Try the jalapeño chicken ramen if you enjoy heat.

Best pediatric dentist in Las Vegas. My son is autistic and has gone from being afraid of the dentist to asking if he can go. The staff is professional and courteous. If you have kids, they should be going here!  Xoxo!
Five star for injectables . Dr. Is really good. Took his time. Very focused and detail oriented.  Will definitely go back if needed again!

Well the one good thing that I can say about Jimmy's is that the older lady who works the front is very kind.

I ordered a standard Gyro. After a few tasteless bites, I noticed that the meat was almost a shade of grey. The sauce was weak and flavorless. The side of fried were like crinkle-cut, obviously frozen, mushy, and undercooked.

Our antipasto salad had sliced generic deli meat, wilted lettuce, and was plain awful. How can you mess up a salad so badly?

My wife ordered the pan seared trout. The trout was obviously previously frozen, overdone, and with an exterior of greasy flour. The vegetables (carrots/peas) had obviously been kept at a appropriate serving temperature for so long that they had become soggy and flavorless-the consistency of canned peas.

The decor needs a Restaurant Impossible makeover. It is dated and tacky. We did like the family historical photos but they were overshadowed by the horrible decor. The plastic covered menus were sticky and dirty.

We will not be back. Seems like a place which lost its mojo.
Fair prices meals with large portions. Each dish includes fresh ingredients with a friendly staff. Try the chicken schwarma!
I think we will be making this place our go to after our morning services.. the meatball caesar salad combo was delicious!!
6 week challenge has begun..5 more to go for a life changing experience. Thanks UFC family!

Well that was a surprise for airport food! Great margaritas and food. Strangely enough, their beans and rice were probably my favorite part of the meal. Drinks are slightly cheaper than most airport selections but a double is $4 more instead of the standard $2.

Food comes out quickly and my server was really chill. He was totally cool with me getting just a margarita but I ended up eating more than I should have. :)

This is a solid choice for theater events in the Queen City.  The Knight Theater is a smaller venue, but they get a great amount of exciting acts that want a more visceral experience with the audience.  The acoustics are great and lighting is handled well.  Staff are friendly and informative.  The venue has a full-bar available.  Bathrooms are easily accessed.

Because the theater is smaller there isn't a bad seat in the house.  It's easy to get to in uptown Charlotte with plenty of parking around and an easy walk from anywhere in the area.  We parked at the Westin and walked up from there.

There are several restaurants in the area for pre- or post-dinner drinks or dinner.

Ill give them 3 stars because the manager did call me and followed up with me after I post my review and apologize for everything. 

I can tell he is good management. And yes my first experience sucked but the food was good I will be trying it again. Giving them another chance. 

I will be updating my Yelp review.

I guess he told everyone what happened because they knew who I was. And I'm ok with that. That's how people learn. We are all human we make mistakes. Saying I'm sorry sometimes is all we need to hear. Thank you 

Updating my stars Joe our server was extremely nice had my food I was taking to go ready when I was done eating my food was amazing came by to check on us. Glad I came back even the girl in the front was nice and made conversation 

Awesome job everyone I definitely had a great 2nd experience.

One of the best restaurants!

Excellent fish n' chips!! The fish is fresh : light and flaky, falls apart when you dive your fork in, not chewy at all. The batter is thin and super crispy. The fries are crispy too and well seasoned. Everything is still burning hot when they serve it to you. I'd love to try the other items next time I go there.

Thank you Georges Z. Markarian, MD and his elite team, everyone in presurgery, PACU and all the nurses and PT that helped me through recovery.  Your skill, teamwork, medical equipment and compassion are globally superior to all other hospitals.  When lost in your hospital, every employee stopped to help provide directions.  The nurses diligently controlled the pain meds down to the minute to make sure there was no unnecessary hardship, food services even went out of their way to make sure food was available to myself and my wife during the most dire of times, use of scanners to find and set an IV on the first try is brilliant, nurses were knowledgeable about the situation and compassionately provided the highest quality of care even at the end of their extremely long shifts. You even walked me to my car after being discharged and continued to care for my recovery until the moment I was in the car. Some hospitals may provide one or two of those qualities, but only Western Reserve Hospital provides all of them. These are just a few of the reasons why I will always come to you in the future when my family needs medical help of any magnitude. Please take these comments seriously. My family has spent more time than most in hospitals in Akron and Cleveland over the past four years and none of them offer the quality of medical services you provide. I've also recovered in less than half the time of others in my situation and that is due to Dr. Georges Z. Markarian, his team and the entire staff at Western Reserve taking all of the extra steps in patient care that most hospitals feel isnt necessary.  Please continue to excel where all others fail so that your standards become the norm. Americans pay a lot of money for healthcare, we should not be neglected and tortured during our most desperate of times. You understand that. Please don't falter and if other hospitals dont follow your lead, buy them.

Auld Dubliner is one of the reasons I wish more people would go to Lake Las Vegas.  It's a typical Irish bar, mostly wooden, smaller tables, but you actually have some room.  It's not crammed together.  We've only been inside, but they have patio seating as well when the weather is nice.

They have an above average selection for beers, with the usual emphasis on Irish and British beers.  I got a flight of testers that was a decent price, given the quality of beers.  The food was above average as well.  Very large serving of fish and chips.  Good batter, but not too thick.  We got chicken fingers (for our 2 year old), and the table liked these as well.  

Service was excellent.  Drinks never reached empty before she was there asking if we wanted another.  There seemed to be several regulars as well, which is rarely a bad sign.  Overall, above average experience, which is saying something, given the number of Irish pubs that have opened in the last few years.  Worth your time.

This place is fine.  You will get a flavorful steak here.  Cooked to your liking.  The sides are great also.  The thick cut fries are not my favorite. Never been a fan of thick cut.  Just eat a baked potato.  It defeats the purpose.
The service was so so.  For what we are paying you would expect the service to be spectacular.  
Overall average but there are much better options out there value and taste wise.
Not as show and tell as Jacobs and Micheals, but still has that show and tell value that people seem to go back for.

Food was good, we ordered breakfast burritos, steak and eggs, and it was all tasty. The inside only has 5 tables so it's probably better for takeout. Staff was friendly and on top of things. Nothing really stood out for me that would make me go out of my way to come back here but it was good, glad I tried it.

I've lived in LV for the better part of a year and spent 6 of those months going from "high-end" salon to "high-end" salon trying to find a stylist with a quality blend of creativity, professionalism, and attention to detail. Every friend recommended their stylist to me, but i was always disappointed by the time my appt was over and I wouldn't end up rebooking. In May I was referred to Chris and within the first 20 mins of my first appointment I was not only impressed but finally excited about a stylist I could trust. By the time the appt was over I felt like I had learned quite a few styling techniques (coming from a guy who has more hair product variety than most girls) and loved my cut! Rebooked. I'm at the point now with Chris where I can walk in, drink my beer, and just let him do what he wants to my hair. He knows what I like and remembers the details of our previous conversations. I'm probably a pain in the ass client for anyone, but Chris definitely is a professional in every sense of he word and never seems annoyed with my picky-ness. He has a client in me for a very long time.

This place keeps going on the decline. Their all you can eat menu is down to a zerox copy with a very limited selection. All they do is make all the other sushi places around Vegas looked so much better.

Great company... Hard workers wouldn't take any breaks even when offered. Worked fast and efficient took very good care of my stuff while moving it. Also better priced then any company in town. I will never move without movers again

PF Chang's is always predictable if you're a regular and have some items that you always stick to or just come to get that special dish. We stopped in for Father's Day during a late lunch hour.  Service was friendly but a bit sluggish for a not-so-full dining room.  Nonetheless the food never disappoints.

For us, starters always include their "famous" lettuce wraps-yummy, crunchy "tacos" without the guilt and full of flavor.  Next on our repertoire are the Lemon Scallops-you won't find these on the menu but if you have a seasoned waiter you should have no problem ordering these-I gave them an extra star for this special request granted.

Another favorite during the summertime heat blazing hours of the day is ordering a refreshing strawberry cooler-not sure this is the exact name but it sounds good to me.  It's a mix of fresh sliced strawberries, cucumbers, mint, sparkling water and some sweet simple syrup. AAAAahhhh. Yum yum will go your tum-tum.

Conveniently located near the airport.
1st time to Shake Shack in downtown Summerlin.  Service was great, burgers were great, strawberry shake and fries were good too.  Quality is very good!

Got to try out this gym with a free guest pass over the weekend.  

This place is N-I-C-E! From the lobby to the change room to the weight room.  

You don't really appreciate a clean and sufficient change room until you have been into a dirty and cramped one.  The change change room had a little lounge area with a tv and couches, hair drying stations, and a steam room (a little tight though).

The training area is really modern so you don't feel like you're in a prison with weights.  Machines and equipments were sufficient and well spaced.  I went on a Saturday morning so the place didn't feel crowded.  Maybe if it was weeknights then I can imagine this place being packed like a sardine can.

I give this gym a 4 star based on a FREE workout and what it is as a gym.  I have no clue what the cost is.  My only complain is that they treat guest like ATM machines and very eager to withdrawal cash from you; they held onto my driving license in front of me until a salesperson came over even after I had asked if I can have my license back.  So just be careful you don't get caught up with preaching and pressuring.

Cheers.

A new concept for a restaurant?  No, it's a hiking route in Red Rock Canyon National Conservation Area.  It's July 5th, and many places are closed, including my gym.  Off to Red Rock this morning hiking.  I parked in the lot where the horse trailers park at the exit from the Scenic Drive.  The hike starts from just inside the exit gate by the parking lot.

The trail was made by horse riders.  It heads toward the Potato Knoll, also known as Wilson's Pimple, the high mound at the base of Mount Wilson.  The trail goes across two dry creek beds, past some petrified wood, and around the back of the Knoll.  When you get to the back of the Knoll, you can take a side trail to the top of the Knoll and get a great view.

Follow the trail around the base of the Knoll and you can't get lost.  It's always good to have a GPS unit with you, and always bring plenty of water when you hike.  It's a desert out there, you know!

An alternative way of doing this hike would be to park at the Oak Creek parking area along SR 159 and hike back to the Knoll along the Oak Creek trail.  Circle the base of the Knoll and then head back.  

The hike is about 5 miles and it took me 2 hours.  There is an elevation gain of only about 150 feet.  It's very gentle.

The photos I have posted are the ones I took today.  If you have any questions about the hike, send me a message.

Happy trails!

This place was our first stop after an early flight in from Seattle, and wanted something light but filling. Not a surprise that the so call "City that never sleep" most restaurants are closed for breakfast/brunch! We happen to stubble upon this place while searching for any opening. Our experience there was great, the owner was friendly (very talkative) and the quality was amazing compare to their price.

Barro's on Indian Bend is my usual family Friday night pizza & wings stop but was looking for something different tonight, but in the same price range. A google search for "best pizza & wings in Scottsdale" lead me to TJ's Pizza & Wings. I'm a NYC pizza fan and that's what the reviews praised here. 

My son and I got there and ordered with the intention of eating our 16" large pizza and 24 wings (for $23.95) there but after sitting down and feeling how slippery the floor was, we decided to get it to go. The slippery (greasy?) floor freaked us out a little, plus there was a good college football game we were missing on a much bigger TV at home.

The guys at the counter were very friendly, wait time was minimal and we picked up drinks at Circle K next door. Another nice convenience was the Redbox machine right outside TJ's front door.

Pizza didn't look as good as I expected it to look after reading all the great reviews but my first bite removed that hint of doubt I had. Great thin crust, cheesy, foldable and a little greasy... Just the way I love it! The other reviews I read about the wings had me pretty anxious to try them out too.  I'm a deep fried crispy wing fanatic and that's exactly how they cooked them. Even after the 5 minute ride home, they were still crispy and drenched in hot sauce, like they should be. Each wing was meaty and decent sized, not like the miniatures I got at Buffalo Wild Wings last weekend (and I love that place).   I would have given TJ's 5 stars if the slices were bigger (large is 16" and as big as they make) and the slippery floor in the dining area didn't freak us out so much! I will definitely be going back for take out. Another nice incentive is that you can save the cutout coupons on the pizza box for a free 16" pizza for every 15 coupons. Thumbs up!

I only eat here for dinner. At lunch time it's to busy. I have the 1/2 chicken with rice and plantains. The chicken is very moist not dried out like some places. The sauces are very good. It's a little small but everybody is friendly. The service is sometimes slow but the food is worth it. I will be back.
One of favorite places. I could eat there everyday. If you go at lunch expect a wait. Don't forget to order those delicious butter cookies. Amazing.

Ummm hello! I love this place! They give you a sample cookie if you're new there, they consider a half dozen to be 7 cookies (yay!), they're fast and friendly, they give you free broken cookies (genius strategy, come on!), and every single cookie I got from there was lip smacking delicious. I will be back!

Bought a few cars and planes from here, destroyed the planes, still racing the cars.  Anytime something breaks we take it in and they will source us a replacement part.  Very helpful staff, great customer service.

I'm sticking with Aldi. Not terribly impressed. A bit of a letdown after such anticipation. 

Messy, low on stock and overall not a good feel 

AND...

Too close to Walmart while not really giving them any competition.  

Disappointed...

This place is the perfect middle ground between classy and casual dining.  And I know what you're thinking, wouldn't it be better to have it one way or another?  I always thought so, but this place changed my mind.

It's located right on the casino floor so you get the feel of being right there in the mix (the casual).  And yet the service, menu selection, and presentation is on such a high level (the classy).  

It's a perfect place to eat before going out at night.  It's high quality food served in an timely manner.  

I was just there with some friends and we ordered a wide variety of dishes.  They were all so good we ended up sharing a lot with one another.  I had the pork chop, which was fantastic, and I was able to try the meatloaf and the burger, both were amazing.  
And then there was this ridiculous appetizer, the truffled potato chips, it's a must!
Dr. Mallinger is the best.  I went to him for years.  He is patient and has a lot of experience.  I was very upset when I changed jobs and could no longer see him.

I wanted to follow up - I figured I would give these guys another try so I called the Pool shop again, to find out about getting the sand in our filter re-done & the owner said "you wrote a bad review about us on yelp so we won't work with you".  I was actually surprised - rather than take the opportunity to  earn my trust back they chose to lose out on potential business.  My husband actually figured out how to change the sand himself - saving us a bunch of money.

Wow... After eating sushi from across the nation i have to say Scottsdale's Geisha A Go Go has surprised me for an ultimate low. Andrew, the manager, reassured us that we had something wrong with our taste buds for not tasting how fresh the fish was here. Insulting to assume. Not recommended!!!!
Absolutely everything I have ever tried here has mad me wish the food would keep coming! Amazing food! love every Eggs benedict special i have tried! You cannot go wrong!
Jesus. Just carpet-bomb the place with bleach. By far the most poorly maintained GoodLife I've ever set foot in. Honestly and this is after filling out at least a half dozen customer service surveys.
Best lasagna ever! Normally never a wait and the food is delicious and melts in your mouth.  Staff are very friendly and attentive. I have been here to many times to count!

We expected this place to be better or at least close to the one in LA. Meat quality was not good. For 2 adults and 2 young kids we order the beef combo for 4-5 people thinking it would be plenty of meat. The portions were small with a lot of fat. Plus the meat quality did not meet the standards of an 8yr old. He said it was tough and chewy. Was not impressed with the service. Would not go back again.

Very tasty San Diego style Mexican food. We have had combo plate with enchiladas and tacos, chimichangas, & carne asada fries. All were  excellent. And they have a salsa bar where you can also get free pickled carrots and jalapeños.  The service is polite and friendly. At dinner time it can get pretty crowded in the dining room where there are a few tables and benches. We have not stayed there to eat but rather got takeout but I don't think it would be a problem eating  there. I am new to the neighborhood but plan on making this one of my go to restaurants!
All around a good place, good food, clean, service is decent. Has a very home like feeling, seemed as all other patrons were enjoying there time there.
Just had their Turkey Devonshire sandwich - in my opinion theirs is the best in Pittsburgh!

I adore this place! The light green walls are serene, the chairs and tables are comfortable, and I love their little brownies with three kinds of chocolate chips in them! The coffee is perfectly smooth and rich, which is the most important thing to get right. (I'm not into masking the taste of burnt espresso with a mocha!) If a place can provide me with a cup of coffee that doesn't taste like it will give me an ulcer, I'll be a fan for life. The only other Pittsburgh place where I've found coffee this delicious was at Commonplace Coffee in Squirrel Hill. I went to college near Chicago and come from California. I count Intelligentsia and Blue Bottle Coffee as some of my favorite places, so I mean it when I say the coffee here is wonderful. Try it out, you won't be let down.

The food is surprisingly good, given the location and the other reviewer's experiences.  It's the kind of place that seems like it would be really inconsistent in both service and food quality.  Last night was a good night- two HUGE salads, 1 Greek, 1 Caesar, both with chix added ($2.50 extra), french bread AND pita- couldn't make up my mind, for just under $22.00.  Oddly, they take cards for food, but not the drinks, and you do have to order food inside at the counter.  Maybe I was in a really flexible mood, cuz that stuff usually flips me out.

If I could rate this place negative stars I would.
The blonde bartender is completely rude. Just tons of attitude, no professionalism at all.
Our lane took forever to get working.. we kept having lane malfunctions until we decided to leave and get a refund. There was 11 of us, and luckily the manager was nice enough to do it for us cause apparently "they never do refunds". I miss the old bartender that was there since I was a child. Oh well, won't be called coming here anymore.

Btw they dont take health cards as an ID!

I have been coming to this salon since I moved to this side of town almost 4 years ago and I can't say enough how much I love it! Everyone is super nice, they do a thorough and complete job on whatever it is you need, and their pricing is competitive to other places. I got acrylic nails removed today and it didn't hurt at all- and in the past it is has always hurt no matter who did them! The nail tech took her time and was very gentle, my nails look great! Love this place.

I have been a long time customer since my childhood days, the service is always friendly and upbeat. Not to mention the delicious burgers and fries. They are open until 1am which makes it fantastic when you're awake at night and feel the need to grab and a double double to go. Every experience I've had is satisfying, I always bring my family to eat here, especially my aunt from Texas who is bewitched by their animal fries. In N Out has a special place in my heart, to remind me of the good times and the great tasty food. Will never get enough of it.

Omg is RIGHT. Hungry and short for time; popped in- FANTASTIC. Perfect balance of everything- flavor, amount of veggies, amount of spice... 
In transient Queen West, thus place should be a longer standing fixture. 
Great service and fresh, delicious healthy food.

This was my first time at this location.
The food was average and a little overpriced.  I feel that they could have a better array of games.  We went on a Saturday around 1:30PM. It was busy and a few birthday parties was going on as well.  Overall, I seriously doubt that I would return to this location.  I could have had more fun at home playing PS4.

Not bad, food is pretty good, the drinks are different and definitely awesome to tryout. 

When I came I had a turkey burger with tofu fries, taste pretty good.

Tried out See & Be Seen after seeing some great reviews online, and they most definitely lived up to the hype! Easy to get to location in Liberty Village, very cool shop interior, great range of eyewear, and an awesome bunch of staff to boot! Their customer service was top notch from the minute I booked my appointment, right up until walking out the door with some fresh new glasses. Special thanks to Janine for helping me find the best fit for my new specs, can't wait to pick them up!
 
This was my first in-depth eye exam, and Dr. Patel and his team make the process very easy and interesting to help you understand all about the health of your eyes. If you're considering getting a check-up or in need of new glasses, 100% pick See & Be Seen.

Thanks guys - Let's go Blue Jays!!

I was seriously injured in a car accident in 2015. The insurance for the person at fault refused to pay a reasonable amount even after my I wn insurance company paid. Gina sued the driver and her insurance company paid her policy limit.  I had over 30,000 in medical bills and Gina helped reduce them so I could get a good settlement.  Thank you Gina for your help.

Probably the best Brooklyn pizza in the area. Can't understand why anybody would go to a chain when they can support local.

Service can be a little spotty when the boss isn't there, and the strip shopping center ambiance leaves a little to be desired.

If the cops eat there, that says a lot.

Stopped in for dinner.Had the brisket sandwich. It was good. 
Stopped in on a rainy Monday evening,was not crowded at all.

For the space it has available, cafe social does a great job. It feels a bit odd as it is in an apartment building lobby but make no mistake, you can get good coffee here. I've been here about 10 times now and every single barista is incredibly kind and informative. Two thumbs up. Downside is there's not great parking is you are driving to this location

In town for Centennial Classic Outdoor games. 

Stopped in for drinks with the wife before heading to our NYE dinner elsewhere.

Let's just say our limited time here was not the best.

Sat at the bar,  as did the family of gnats.   One was in my wife's drink when it was brought and no one seemed to care when we mentioned how plentiful they were.

 (New drink was brought).

Paid our bill and left.

Aria is a relatively new addition to the York/Bremner strip (just 9 months young).  It is located in a great location (which also means that if there are events going on at the ACC that you might end up paying $25 for parking! Ouch.)  My word of advice?  Look for the Green P at 10 York Street (which doesn't look like it will be there very long as it looks like a condo development is going up in its place).  We were lucky enough to have nabbed the last spot and paid $4 for parking.

Tucked away in the corner of the Telus Tower you will find the entrance to Aria.  It has a very Manhattan feel to it with high ceilings, big glass windows that faces the Maple Leaf Square and trendy seating.  The chairs are quite comfortable, and the Damask sofa seats are chic!

I made a reservation online and the only time available was later in the evening.  I was rather upset when I showed up to the restaurant and there were quite a few empty tables.  I like to eat dinner earlier, rather than later.

A complimentary coat check is available though the hostess was less than stellar. She left us unattended for a few minutes before reappearing.  However, another server (who I later found out is the pioneer behind the Cocktail Menu) aided us.

We were seated in the corner with a great view of Maple Leaf Square.  The service here is very lax and this is definitely a place you could spend hours at without being hustled out the door.  

After having perused the cocktail menu I decided on La Motta, which is a vodka-based drink with fresh yuzu, peach simple syrup and rosemary.  To my surprise, my cocktail was salty?  I don't think I was so hungry that my taste buds went awry, but my DC also concluded that my drink was salty.  When prompted about how our cocktails were I mentioned I didn't like it, and the Ryan Gosling look-a-like cocktail pioneer said he'd whip me up another cocktail personally.  This time I opted for the Dahlia.  While I did say I wanted something sweeter, this was TOO sweet.  It was like drinking a minty maple syrup.  The presentation of the cocktails were pretty, but suffice it to say that I nursed my sweet cocktail like a child forced to drink carrot juice.  The Sazerac that my DC ordered was definitely a man's drink as it was S-T-R-O-N-G (Rye whiskey-based drink).  My word of advice, order a wine instead.  They have an impressive display of wines that go from floor to ceiling (and that is one HIGH ceiling).  

A trio of bread was brought out.  A French, an Italian and a Focaccia.   The Focaccia was by far my favourite as it was crusty on the top, but spongy throughout.  It was a Rosemary bread, and was very good with the spreadable butter.

For starters we ordered the Carne Cruda served with a raw egg, black truffle and Porcini fries.  This knocked my socks off.  This is what a steak tartare should be like.  Tender, just the right amount of salt, and just the right amount of pickled tang.  It didn't even need pepper.  The raw egg added a luxurious, creamy texture to the dish.  And the fries, although there were only 5 of them, were divine.

For mains we opted for the Bigoli alla Bottarga which was a thick noodle served with garlic, chillies, roasted tomatoes, herbs and Bottarga di Muggine which is a cured roe of grey mullets.  The thick noodles were a very firm pasta.  I just kept chewing and chewing and chewing at it.  The tomatoes were pleasantly sweet, but I didn't care too much for the bitter aftertaste of the Bottarga.  

The Deboned Partridge served atop a bed of Fregola Sarda, porcini bread stuffing, bay leaf essence, chestnuts and fig puree.  Fregola Sarda is a type of Sardinian pasta that loosely resembles Israeli Couscous but has the texture of a Spaetzle.  It was very savoury and complemented the crisp-skinned deboned partridge very well.  I don't know that I would've chosen partridge as it is a much more muscular bird, which means a tougher meat.  

For dessert we were disappointed to learn that the Napolean and Chocolate Eclairs were sold out for the night, so we opted for the Buddino.  In hindsight, I probably should've taken the sold-out options as a cue that they were the best in the house and opted out of dessert.  Oh well.  The Buddino was served with a Mascarpone cheese.  It was quite the unconventional "pudding" as it was more like a flourless chocolate cake encased with a tart pastry.  The chocolate flavour was quite weak as it but lingered for a mere second in your mouth before disappearing altogether and if there was any chestnut, it was lost.  The tart shell was chewy.  I think this dish is lost somewhere between a flourless chocolate cake and a brownie.  

Verdict:
I would recommend Aria for its service and ambiance before its food.  The food may not be suitable for those who are the "meat and potatoes" type and non-experimental as they use untraditional ingredients.  Some of the food was wonderfully executed while tweaks were needed for others.

Definitely will not be returning here.  The guy who did my mom's nails was rude and arrogant. The lady who did my nails did not even introduce herself and made it seem as though I ruined her day by coming in.  I have cuts on every finger, the nails are misshapped, and the polish is bulky.  He was also arguing with a customer who he made wait while her nail technician helped another customer who got there after her.  I would definitely think twice before coming here if you are looking for a nail place in Gilbert.
All the tables have a great view and despite de fact the place was full for Thursday night football, the waitress was on point with our drinks.

I agree with Krysta, the earlier reviewer. I stayed here many many times when it was a Loews so I immediately chose it for my cousins, sister and I to stay for my sister's bachelorette weekend. What a complete and utter disappointment. 

I won't go into detail but I ran into road blocks and poor service with literally EVERY aspect of our stay. And even after the very small gesture they gave, providing us with one complimentary cocktail each, the drink bill showed up on my final statement and had to go to the front desk at 6am before we left for the airport to clear up the charge, which took about a half hour. Thanks, but no thanks. 

I thought about giving it just one star, but the property is beautiful (everything looks identical from when it was Loews) so that's worth one more star. While I'll never stay here again,  I'd say if you're going for the lovely lakeside views, go, but don't expect anything in terms of service.
Good fresh food and kind of nice take on an old fried the rice bowl.  Love the options and will need to sample a few more on future trips.

Leslie Cintron was the service tech today 11/1318.
Very friendly, helpful, polite.
Knew what she was doing, and got it done, quickly and efficiently.
Took the time to explain what was done.

Living in a place that has tons of sand and no ocean...it is nice to find somewhere that you can escape and feel like you're at the beach. The surfing videos playing on the TV's trick you into thinking that you are looking out a window with an ocean view.

Fish tacos are what I always order. They are huge!! I forget that I only need one but they are so delicious I have now problem eating both. Price might seem high but they are made with quality fish that is grilled perfectly!

If you haven't been you should!! It is like a little mini lunch vacation!!
Not everything is 5 star- but most is. Best value with great food. Have been at least 10 times and always look forward to coming back. Skipped Mastros one evening and went here and didn't look back.

The atmosphere and decor bring me straight to Thailand. I love how even down to the small details such as dishes and utensils are what you would use to eat in Thailand. 

We ordered the , Labb calamari, chicken pad Thai, red curry and the Si Lom Soi 4 bucket drink and Thai iced tea. Everything was great and the drink was very fun and tasted good as well. With the calamari dish you should eat it together with the red onions because the flavours just pop in your mouth.

I would definitely come back and try the green curry. 

Also, I went on a Tuesday evening at 6:30 and it wasn't busy but an hour later it was a full house!

I'm not even going to start. 
The bed was comfortable and it was close to the Sands Convention Center. 
Other than that BAAAAH

We've used several landscapers over the years and the quality of their work deteriorated over time. ... Arrived late. ... Missed the details, etc. 

AMS Landscaping gave us an extremely reasonable quote and do a fantastic job, week-in and week-out. Very thorough. Their staff is friendly and easy to work with. I highly recommend them for your landscaping needs.

So this place is on my route to work & I follow the las Vegas hashtag on Instagram & I always see how lovely & photogenic the chicken  sandwich looks......  The photos don't do it justiceeeeee. Chicken was plump & juicy white meat, flavors were there lettuce was crisp.... Just a well put together sandwich to say the least.
Had a good time. Good vibes good music. Ballantyne is a really nice area. There was enough parking. The music was fun but I had the hookah outside

This place always treats me like VIP when I go there and always welcoming and polite. 

Never have a problem getting an appt scheduled and their wait times aren't very long as previous dentists I've been to in the past.

This place is right next door to my house.  We came here when they first opened up and fell in love with it ever since.  Every dining experience has been excellent - the service is always friendly and attentive and food perfectly cooked/prepared.   We did a few ala cartes but most of the time it's always AYCE, both lunch and dinner.  Heck if they had breakfast I would do that too.  

Most sushi places have a few items that are exceptional and a few not so great, but everything here range from good to phenomenal.  

Let me talk a bit about their sashimi items.  I love sashimis and this place has some of the best sashimis i've ever eaten.  Their Seared Albacore with crispy onion in ginger sauce is oh so heavenly.  The only  problem is their sashimis are not included with the AYCE menu and that's understandable because the sashimis are pricier.  Another one is the Yellowtail sashimi with jalapeno and ponzu sauce.  OMG this melts in your mouth and it should be called screaming orgasm for your mouth!  amazing stuff!  How about this "Tuna sashimi with shaved daikon in a chef special sauce"? Everytime i finish this plate I want to lick the sauce off the plate but there's always people around me.  

Now for their rolls.  They make the typical rolls like Rainbow, Dragon, Spider, Dynamite and Catepillar taste amazing.  Flavor explosion with every bite.  They have a few rolls that are wrapped in thin soy paper sheet that are not as filling as the ones with rice.  Some days I do low carb and i would order a bunch of these.  Pink Lady and Oh My Heart are my favorites.  If you like scallop make sure you order the Volcano, baked scallop with yum yum sauce.  

Side dishes and appetizers are very small when you order with AYCE and that's a good thing cuz you just want to taste the variety of stuff.  Finish off with some mochi's and you can die happy.

Gordon needs to be fired from the kitchen.  We ate here last Friday (party of 6) and felt like we were rushed through the entire evening.  All food items we tasted epwere very mediocre and prices were off the chart.  $30 for the fish and chips and $22 for the burger which was unimaginative and small in size.  Even the beer and wine were overpriced for a pub.  We ate here out of convenience because we were staying in Caesar's but will not return as there are far better places in the Linq area and other hotels across the street.  Gordon must be making a high profit margin on this restaurant.
So good! Fresh ingredients, great salsa bar... stoked to have such a great taco spot come to our neighborhood

Ok, I get it, you get what you pay for.. but I left the gym after 10 minutes today. I literally could not work out because every treadmill is BROKEN (for weeeeks now). I finally found a treadmill that was working and I almost fell off because it was shaking SO much. Fine, whatever. I went to the ellipticals instead, and after three minutes the machine, on its own, went from level 1 to 25 in three seconds! So I once again went to the front desk to complain and let them know about it. I'm sure they know me by now. 

I figured I would try to work out using some of the equipment in the women's dungeon. Hot as balls, terrible green lighting, more broken machines, and the lady next to me smelled like an ashtray. 

Maybe you would like to use the weight machines instead? Great, well good luck trying to find a machine with pins in it. That is also a very common issue at this gym. Perhaps you would like to do your own work out in the fitness room when classes aren't going on, well, too bad because they lock it up so you're left to stretch in the tiny area right outside the fitness room, or.. back to the dungeon instead. 

Want to sanitize your hands? Sure, there is NEVER any sanitizer actually IN the container on the wall. 

Why I like this gym? It's close to my house. The staff is also nice, but nice doesn't give me a workout. I get more frustrated AT the gym than anything else. Not good. 

Ps, thanks for investing in the lobby area with your new meals to go!.... much better new equipment, right? (Obvious sarcasm there)

They did an UNSATISFACTORY job and did not honor their 100% guarantee. This company we hired on a $49 direct ad special. When we called/emailed and complained to the Supervisor/Owner, they said they would handle it. They never as much as returned my calls, emails to proceed with the issues at hand. We are left with a half clean and half dirty home because of this. I stand to lose my security and cleaning fee deposit with my landlord if not rectified. We are on our hands and knees trying to clean these filthy spots with over the counter cleaners to try and remove the dirty stains that remain. We have turned them over to the BBB and have asked for a full refund of services that they did not guarantee. DO NOT USE THIS COMPANY, they present themselves as a FRAUD. And Owner Esvin R, you have the unmitigated gall to refer to customers who dislike your service LIARS. I hope and pray they take your company to small claims. You should be put out of business for the practices you perform. Slam dunk.  And to the person who's white carpet turned pink, please take the time to take these people to small claims and mitigate your damages.
